title: banana-mango bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Whip butter and sugar together and add to dry mixture.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: biscuits (buttermilk)(grandmother's)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and soda together.
Add shortening.
Mix together.
Add milk.
Bake at 450° to 500°.
Put grease on top.

title: shrimp souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add tomato soup and mayonnaise; whip.
When syrupy, add green pepper and shrimp; mix.
Pour into mold or individual serving dishes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread in bowl with onion, bell pepper, tomato and bacon.
Mix together mayonnaise, mustard and spices.
Pour mixture over cornbread and stir gently.
Chill before serving.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill for 30 minutes before serving.

title: pesto tarte
directions: In food processor to make pesto sauce, blend basil, garlic, grated cheese, oil and pine nuts till smooth.
In food processor, mix
softened cream cheese, mascarpone cheese and butter. Line a mold with dampened cheese cloth.
Layer cheese mixture, then pesto, etc., finishing with cheese.
Fold cloth over mold. Refrigerate 2-3 days before serving.
Serve at room temp, but unmold when cold.
Serve with fried Italian bread or crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat with spoon. In separate bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Slowly add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from pan; cool and cut.

title: divinity
directions: Cook 3 cups sugar and 3/4 cup water until it forms a thread; add slowly to well beaten egg whites.
While you are doing this, take 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water, then add to first mixture. Beat and beat.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Beat eggs and fruit cocktail.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Spread evenly into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix nuts and brown sugar.
Sprinkle on cake.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°, then 10 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: caramel corn micro
directions: Prepare shell with 3/4 cup cooked rice.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Combine all ingredients except wings.
Marinate wings for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: nut cream drops
directions: Mix sugar, milk and corn syrup.
Boil until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire and cool slowly 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add nuts and drop on oiled paper.

title: apple butter(delicious on toast, pound cake or biscuits.)
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Put into an 8-quart pot (seeds, stems and all) with apple cider.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until very tender.
Put apples through a food mill or sieve set over a large bowl, pressing on solids with a spoon. Discard solids.
Return puree to pot.

title: chicken farfalle alfredo with broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli; set aside.
Cook pasta.
Saute chicken in oil until browned (large skillet); take out.
Saute pepper in oil. Add whipping cream, 1 cup Parmesan and Monterey Jack cheese. Simmer until thickens.
Add pasta and broccoli.
Simmer.
Put remaining Parmesan when serving.

title: artichoke-green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, artichoke hearts, mushrooms and bread crumbs. Add cheese and lemon juice; mix.
Spoon into baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top; dot with margarine.
Bake in regular oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt
cheese
in
top
of
double
boiler.
Combine all ingredients
in
mixing
bowl.
Knead with fingers until thoroughly mixed.
Form into small balls about 1-inch in diameter. Bake
on
cookie sheets at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You may make balls ahead of time and store in refrigerator or freezer. Also
good	reheated.
Good for breakfast, snacks and as appetizers.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix and serve with chips.

title: quick veggie dip
directions: Mix well in blender and chill for 1 hour.
Use with veggies and chips.

title: pork cacciatore
directions: Brown pork in oil in skillet over medium heat.
Remove pork and set aside.
Add peppers and onions to drippings.
Cook until lightly browned.
Return pork to skillet.
Add tomato sauce and next 4 ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling. Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Stir in cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: crab and cheese puffs
directions: Drain the crab meat and grate the cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on small roll halves.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes, until brown.

title: lo-cal banana split cake
directions: Melt butter, then add crushed crackers to make crust.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple.
Mix pudding according to directions, then layer over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle chocolate over.
This makes a cool and lite dessert for all the family.

title: no bake cake
directions: Break sponge cake into small pieces.
Line cake dish.
Prepare pudding and let set about 3 minutes. Pour over cake pieces.
Let set about 3 minutes. Spread fruit over pudding and cake mixture. Top with whipped cream.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in pan over low heat.
Blend flour and salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
In greased 2-quart casserole, layer in following order:
Potatoes, onions, sauce and ham (if desired) and repeat.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover; bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 30 to 45 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix drained kidney beans, butter beans and pork and beans together with mixture of catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire and onion.
Add crumbled bacon, reserved bacon drippings and hamburger to bean mixture.
Place all in casserole dish.
Top with 4 slices cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal jelly bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put half of the mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread jelly over dough. Sprinkle remaining dough over layer of jelly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Cool pan on rack. Cut 24 bars.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine with tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, pimiento, salt, pepper and peas.
Blend soup with milk; heat through.
Add 1/2 of cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add to cooked noodles, tuna and rest of the ingredients (except almonds).

title: bavarian sauerkraut
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Rinse sauerkraut in warm water; drain.
Combine sauerkraut, onion, pork pieces and rest of the ingredients in large pan.
Cover and bake in oven at least 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally, and if needed, add a little more liquid.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour
the
eggs,
milk, vanilla and salt over the bread and brown sugar in double boiler.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brandon's banana-nana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 3 cups skim milk.
Fold in half of whipped topping.
Reserve 6 Nilla wafers and 1 banana.
Slice remaining bananas.
Arrange a layer of wafers on bottom of a 2-quart round baking dish or bowl.
Spread 1/4 pudding over wafers; top with banana slices.
Place wafers around sides of dish.
Continue layering wafers, pudding and bananas, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill 3 hours, or until serving time.
Slice remaining banana.
Garnish with banana slices, remaining 6 wafers and whipped topping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: northumberland salad
directions: Pour the pineapple, undrained, into a bowl with pudding and mix well.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Stir until mixed. Refrigerate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large glass bowl, place lettuce, then layer celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise to edge sealing all.
Sprinkle sugar, then layer bacon and cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until serving.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: mother's good potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 1-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook
noodles
in
boiling
water until tender, about 5 minutes;
drain.
Mix
together
the
soup
and milk, then add cheese
and
olives.
Put this mixture and noodles back in the pan you cooked the noodles.
Mix everything thoroughly.
Heat until cheese has melted.
You may put the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole and bake 20 minutes in an oven set at 375°.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon strips into small pieces.
Fry bacon pieces until golden brown.
Place bacon and bacon grease along with all other ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salami of duck
directions: Mix well and let set a few minutes; serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients
and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: never fail souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cube.
In a medium casserole, alternate cheese slices and bread.
Begin and end with bread. Beat together milk, eggs and salt.
Pour over layers.
Let stand overnight.
Put casserole in a pan of hot water in a 400° oven and bake for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water together until sugar and yeast dissolve.
Set aside.
Mix flour, salt and Crisco together very well and knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Lightly grease top and sides of dough; cover and let rise in warm place until 3 times its original size.
Roll out about 1-inch thick; spread entire dough with soft butter and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Fold into 1/2 moon and place in greased pan.
Let rise again until double its size before baking at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wassail
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Strain off spices.
Good for crock-pot.
May use less of the sugars.

title: yokefellow casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles; mix well.
Then stir in noodles.
Top with cheese or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato sausage casserole
directions: Remove skin from sausage; crumble.
Brown and drain.
Place layer of sausage in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of sweet potatoes and layer of marshmallows.
Continue with layer of sausage, potatoes and marshmallows.
Sprinkle with orange juice and brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Pour punch over sherbet in bowl.
Punch will get cool as sherbet melts.
Great punch for Christmas.

title: hot sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Makes around 10 pints.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until done.
Store in airtight container and it lasts indefinitely.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Cut 2 frying chickens.
Arrange skin-side up on roasting pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in enough hot water to cover the bottom of the pan.
Peel and slice large onion and arrange on chicken.
Place uncovered in oven for 1/2 hour at 275°.
Take out and turn over and bake another 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and turn skin-side up again.
Pour mesquite sauce over the chicken. Bake 1 hour longer; baste with sauce frequently.

title: how to cook a christmas turkey
directions: Stuff with celery and peanut butter.
Cook 45 hours at 20°. Serve with coffee and lemonade.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fish marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate fish at least 30 minutes. Grill 5 to 10 minutes on high, depending upon thickness.
Fish is done when flakes with fork and the "slimy jello look" is gone.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
While noodles cook, combine corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Drain noodles and toss with oil.
Add noodles to soup mixture and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with additional Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix coconut in. Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Build up slight edge.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add milk and butter.
Cool until very thick, stirring constantly.
Set pan in cold water to cool.

title: lemon snaps(cookies)
directions: Mix sugar and butter until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place teaspoons of dough on pan, leaving much room for expansion.
(Snaps come out about 4 inches in diameter.)
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: chili pasta grande
directions: Spray large skillet with Pam.
Heat over medium heat.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes. Add undrained chopped tomatoes, kidney beans, jalapeno pepper, chili powder and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Toss with cooked macaroni. Garnish with sour cream, if desired.
Serve with bread sticks, Mexican cornbread or cornsticks and a salad.
Ole.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease 9 x 13 inch pan. Dump undrained pineapple and swirl to fill corners. Dump cherry pie filling - push around until layer of fruit is almost even. Dump cake mix and sprinkle with nuts. Cut oleo in patties and place on top. Do not mix. Bake 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Pour melted margarine over flour.
Press into 14-inch pizza pan to make a crust around edge to hold strawberry mixture.
Press pecan pieces on pizza pan, covering flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread pie crust with butter or margarine.
In medium skillet, over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels; crumble.
Sprinkle bacon in pie crust.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Put marshmallows and strawberry juice in 2 quart saucepan. Over low heat, cook and stir just until marshmallows melt.
Cool. Add drained strawberries and pineapple.
Whip cream until stiff. Using the same beaters, blend together the softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gently fold together whipped cream and cream cheese mixture.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour into 8 inch square pan or 12 paper lined cupcake pans.
Freeze until firm. Cover well to store.

title: tangy apple cherry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add applesauce and orange juice.
Pour into individual molds or one large mold.

title: frozen corn
directions: Cut corn from the ears.
Place in a roaster pan with the butter and cream.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and put into containers.
Freeze.

title: sour cream pineapple coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple and sour cream.
Mix well and turn into a well greased and floured, fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, drizzle topping on top of cake.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together.
Let cool; when cool enough to touch, add nuts and marshmallows.
Roll into a ball. Separate into three parts and form a ball with each.
Then make each ball into a cylindrical roll.
Roll in coconut.
Slice and serve after 24 hours.
This requires no cooking.

title: strawberry cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except preserves.
Form into ball.
Pour preserves over the top and chill.
Serve with party crackers or spread very thin layer on sliced ham and roll into pinwheels.

title: kari-kare(meat and vegetable stew in peanut sauce)
directions: Place oxtail pieces in large pot; add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and flavoring; mix well.
Bake at 325° in a tube pan, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: praline topped yams
directions: Whip the potatoes while hot. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with following mixture and bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab leg dinner
directions: In large pot, boil water, 1 lemon, onion, potatoes and crab boil for 30 minutes.
Add crab legs; boil for another 17 minutes. Add corn; boil for another 6 minutes, or until corn is done. Drain and serve with melted butter and lemon wedges.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Drain off as much water as possible. Beat eggs slightly.
Put into grated potatoes. Add salt.
Add flour a little at a time while stirring.
Fry in greased skillet until golden brown on both sides. Makes about 10 pancakes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot in order listed. Stir once; turn pot to low and cook overnight.
Remove chicken from bones.
Also remove bay leaf.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil. Add grated carrots. Sift together soda, baking powder, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add to carrot mixture. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, sour milk, flour, salt, apples, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, blend together cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
When cake is done, poke holes throughout cake with a fork (while cake is still hot).
Pour liquid mixture over cake.
Cool completely.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.

title: corky's cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and lay oleo in covered container until soft. Add flour, salt and cayenne to creamed mixture.
Work into a smooth ball.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Mix in pepperoni.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer spaghetti sauce, meat, cheese and pasta.
Make three layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and roll into bite-size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 80.

title: the classic french omelet
directions: Heat pan over medium-high heat.
Melt butter.
Pour in eggs. Stir with fork, drawing edges to center.
As eggs begin to set, tilt pan to make sure it's not sticking.
Using fork, start rolling.
Turn out on plate, seam side down.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
In large bowl combine the soups, undrained green chiles and ground beef mixture. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 cup soup mixture over bottom. Tear 1/2 of tortillas into pieces about 3 x 3 inches and randomly place overlapping in pan.
Spoon 1/2 of soup mixture over this. Cover with 1 cup cheese.
Tear and randomly place remaining tortillas over this.
Cover with remaining soup mixture.
Pour enchilada sauce over top.
Take large, sharp knife and make 6 to 8 "cuts" down into casserole so that enchilada sauce "leaks" down into casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes until all is light brown and "bubbly." Take out of oven and let set about 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple (undrained); add sugar and mix well.
When cooled, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate to gel.

title: meatless spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onions, celery, green pepper and eggplant together in food processor.
Saute in large pan, using oil.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon, tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings to taste. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Best made a day ahead.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put milk in it and stir.
Put ice in it.
Mix it together. Put some sugar in it.
Stir it.
Put flour in it.
Put in some butter.
Put ice in it.
Put strawberries on the pie.
Put icing, cornmeal, hot chocolate and eggs.
Stir it and put in the oven. Turn the oven on.
Half it and eat it.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add all ingredients except crackers crumbs.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle with the crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: spicy almonds and cashews
directions: In a small heavy skillet, melt the butter over moderately low heat; add the cumin, chili powder, cayenne, salt and paprika and cook the spices, stirring, for 30 seconds.
Add the nuts and stir them to coat well.
Transfer coated nuts into a baking pan, large enough to hold them in one layer and toast them in a preheated 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let the nuts cool and transfer them to a serving dish.
Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown in oil ground beef and onions.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 2 hours.

title: chicken continental
directions: Melt butter and oil in a large skillet.
Add the onions; cook slowly until soft.
Add the chicken pieces; cook until lightly browned on all sides.
Remove the chicken from the pan.
Stir in the vermouth and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and stir in the tomato paste, cinnamon and salt to taste.
Return the chicken to the pan.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: duelin' grits
directions: Combine grits, eggs, margarine and salt.
Layer into baking dish with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until puffy and browned.
This recipe can be easily doubled.

title: joe's salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, cilantro, green onions, garlic, peppers and avocado.
Mix and chill.

title: fry bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use enough water to make a soft dough (not sticky).
Let stand for at least 1/2 hour.
(The longer it stands, the better.)
Cut into small pieces.
Flatten into rounds or other shapes to your liking.
Heat oil until hot.
Place about 3 or 4 pieces of dough at a time in pan with oil and fry until done. It is done when golden brown all over.
Makes 8 or 9 rolls.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in cold water for 2 hours.
Pack in sterilized jars.
To each jar, add grape leaves, garlic cloves, dill and a pinch of alum.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal at once.

title: avocado lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 3/4 cup cold water and lime or lemon juice. Chill until syrupy.
Combine mashed avocado and sour cream.
Blend into thickened gelatin. Refrigerate until firm.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper together.
Drain. Add tomato juice, beans and chili powder.
Cook slowly for 1 hour or until mixture thickens.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet.
Cook at medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar.
Place saucepan in bowl of cold water.
Beat until smooth and spreading consistency.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with baking powder, salt and milk, alternating.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lace cookie baskets
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, cooking until sugar is dissolved. Add flour, almonds and salt.
Stir one minute.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Beat until milk is absorbed and drop from teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
(Use only a baking sheet with a nonstick Teflon coating and butter only the first batch.)
Bake 3 cookies at a time at 325° for 3 to 5 minutes or until barely brown.
Remove from sheet as soon as you can get a spatula under the cookie.
Work fast and mold cookie over the bottom of a glass tumbler to form a basket.
Makes 12 cookies.

title: creamy lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool and add all other ingredients. Chill until firm in 9-inch pan.

title: k d puffy paint(for pleasure only! do not eat!)
directions: Mix equal parts of flour, salt and water in a bowl; add tempera.
Pour mixture into plastic squeeze bottles.
Show the children how to squeeze the puffy paint onto paper in lines or dots.
Encourage to experiment with different designs and patterns.
Puffy paint hardens when it dries, approximately 24 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake as directed on package.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed until smooth and creamy.
Spread on crust.
Top with veggies like:
broccoli, cherry tomatoes, onions, green peppers, celery, carrots and yellow squash.
Refrigerate.
Cut into serving squares.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs, oil, and sugar. Add milk, stir - add dry ingredients. Stir well. Add blueberries to batter. Mix in with other ingredients. Fill muffin cups 1/2 full and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar and baking soda. Add egg.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into muffin pans or use paper liners.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes, then 30 to 35 minutes at 350° (center is slightly less set).
Top with whipped cream.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, chopped corned beef, finely chopped pickles and onion together.
Spread onto tortillas and roll.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch pieces.
Serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients
Add oil and stir well. Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add carrots. Bake in 3 layer cake pans at 350°.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add the rest of ingredients. Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Mix with mixer flour, sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix by hand remaining ingredients with spoon.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, for 75 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix into this mix, peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Add this to mixture.
Use 1/2 of each ingredient for 1 pie.
Use 2 chocolate or graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
Can top pie with Cool Whip if desired.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Combine green beans, whole tomatoes, hot tomatoes, bacon drippings, onion and salt in a bean pot.
Cook beans slowly for 30 minutes.
Makes a wonderful side dish for a spicy entree.

title: rye crisps dog biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven to
Blend	flours.
Mix
oil
with water and add to flour.
Mix
well.
Dough should form a ball. Pat out dough to
inch
thickness on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Cut with doggie biscuit cutter and remove scraps.
Pat out scraps and proceed
as before.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cook on wire rack.

title: fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix fruit and nuts in and decorate with cherries.
Make in a loaf pan. Refrigerate before turning out of pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone; save 1 cup broth.
Brown onion and pimento in oil; cut off heat.
Add spaghetti, chicken, soup, salts and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well with broth.
Put in a casserole dish and top with other 1/2 of cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° until golden brown on top, about 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble.
Drain canned beans and mix all ingredients together.
Put into large baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or put in a crock-pot and heat well.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Boil hamburger and water for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Place ingredients in blender in order given, one at a time. Mix well after each addition.
Pour mixture into a well buttered 10-inch pie pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
The crust will be on the bottom, the custard in the center and the coconut on top. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans. Put into rounded bowl and chill. Turn upside down into serving plate and coat outside with pecans. (Could be shaped into a ball or in a dish with the pecans on top.)

title: green enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in double boiler.
Brown the ground beef and green onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain and add cheese.
Roll in tortillas.
Pour cheese sauce over tortillas.
Heat in 300° to 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Put into baking dish.
Pour water into pan to get juices from the brownings.
Pour over meat.
Add wine and soups.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Add vegetables (carrots, onions, peas and potatoes).
Bake 1 hour more.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat again.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt, apples and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes in 9-inch pie tin at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: banana loaf
directions: Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until it tests done, 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together in a large bowl. Use 2 heaping teaspoons to one cup boiling water.
Stor in a covered container.
Makes a nice gift for a friend!

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or cook in slow cooker for 2 to 3 hours on low.

title: colored popcorn
directions: Use a large pan and cook on high heat until ingredients boil. Remove from heat and stir in popcorn.

title: spanish sauce for chili
directions: Boil peppers in enough water to cover them until soft.
Mash or press through colander.
Add all other ingredients.
Pack into clean hot jars, partly seal and process in water for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Add
all
ingredients
together in a large mixing bowl. Mix for
minutes.
Turn
into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas dessert
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Pat in bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: special k bars
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Press into 9 X 13 pan.
Pour melted chocolate chips over top.

title: zucchini alla cece
directions: Heat oil in a medium-size skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, zucchini, basil and thyme.
Cook, covered, for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, chickpeas and black pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until zucchini is just tender.
Refrigerate for up to 3 days.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, milk and orange flavoring.
Stir in flour.
Add cornflakes and pecans, mixing well.
Drop from a a tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Put pineapple, undrained and lemon pudding mix into a bowl. Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine
all
these ingredients except 2 cans of tomato sauce and
brown
sugar.
Put
in
Pyrex oblong casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle brown sugar and top with 2 cans of tomato sauce.
Bake
with foil on top at 350° for 1 hour, then take foil off to brown.

title: snack dip
directions: On a luncheon plate (medium size), spread cream cheese.
Spread shrimp on that.
Spread shrimp cocktail sauce on that.
Delicious spread on crackers, especially Bretons.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Roll into ball or log, then roll in mixture of pecans, chili powder and paprika.
Yields 1 cheese ball.

title: waffle stack
directions: Spread 1 waffle with cottage cheese; top with second waffle. Spread with cottage cheese.
Top with fruit.
Serve with maple syrup, if desired.
Makes 1 serving.

title: wilda's peanut butter pie(so easy!)
directions: Mix softened oleo with graham cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix partially softened ice cream, peanut butter and Cool Whip together; pour into crust.
Freeze well.
Cut into serving pieces and serve.

title: hawaiian ham spread
directions: Mix together until smooth. Serve on sliced Hawaiian bread.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Place in layers in the order given in a greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil while baking.
Remove cover last 15 minutes and dot with cheese.
Serves 12.

title: german dinner
directions: Layer ingredients as given in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pan am pork chops
directions: Crush oregano, parsley, garlic and salt together.
Add lemon juice and 1 tablespoon oil; mix well.
Brush on both sides of pork chops; let stand 10 minutes.
Brown chops in remaining oil in skillet, then remove chops.
Add onion and tomatoes to skillet; cook until onion is soft.
Add raw rice; stir until well coated with oil.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Return chops to skillet. Cover; simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken "divine"
directions: Sprinkle
chicken with rosemary, salt and pepper.
Bake chicken at
for
1 hour.
Cool.
Skin, debone and slice. Cook broccoli
in
water
with
salt and onion.
Drain.
Layer chicken, then
broccoli, then rice in buttered casserole dish. Pour Cheese
Sauce over entire dish.
Add more grated Parmesan on top if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: andrea's dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Keep until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill (overnight is best).
Form into a ball and roll in a mixture of pecans and parsley.
Yields about 15 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.

title: cheese and onion pastries
directions: Combine cheese and soup.
Separate dough into 10 triangles. Cut in 1/2 diagonally.
Fill and fold. Brush with oil and sprinkle with dill. Bake at 375° for 13 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in pumpkin.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: gurgling cucumber salad(germany)
directions: Chill cream.
Wash and grate cucumbers; sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Add vinegar; allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Add sweet cream; mix.
Add pepper if desired.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Heat 15x20 air cookie sheet for 3 minutes at 360°.
Roll out dough on hot cookie sheet.
Score with 2 1/2x3 card.	Bake until barely brown.
Yield 25 pieces.

title: marshmallow cinnamon rolls
directions: 1st Layer:
Slice
tube Pillsbury sugar cookie dough thin and press on pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: glacier cucumber salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, celery, green pepper and green onions. Blend tofu, salad dressing, apple cider vinegar, mustard and sweetener together.
Mix well.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, dill, celery seed, etc.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms, then combine all the ingredients in a crock-pot; simmer for 4 to 6 hours.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, garlic, shallots and oil; toss to coat. Spread on a full sheet pan and roast in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Toss hot roasted potato mixture in dressing with rosemary, thyme and pepper.
Serve warm.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Put in bottom of pie shell.
Mix other ingredients and pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sandwich spread(mom's)
directions: Grind enough green tomatoes to make 1 pint without juice. Grind peppers.
Mix the tomatoes, peppers and salt together. After a few minutes drain off juice.
Put in kettle with 1/2 cup water and boil until tender.
Add 1/2 dozen ground sweet pickles to the tomatoes and peppers.
Keep hot until the following dressing is prepared.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix together and chill.

title: linguine with summer squash and tomatoes
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Add squash during last 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain pasta and squash. Transfer immediately to bowl with tomato mixture.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
Nutrient value per serving: 348 calories, 12 g. protein, 10 g. fat, 55 g. carbonhydrates, 384 mg. sodium, 4 mg. cholesterol.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Place onion rings in the unbaked pie shell.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over the onion rings.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook and drain cabbage.
Mix all ingredients together with cabbage except butter and crackers.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew (italian style)
directions: Saute onions and meat in shortening until meat is browned. Add water; cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours until meat is tender. Add potatoes, carrots, celery, tomatoes, bay leaves, salt, pepper, bouillon and garlic.
Add enough water to cover vegetables. Simmer about 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: chicken stuffed with potatoes and olives
directions: In a large bowl, place the potatoes, olives, rosemary, parsley, garlic, anchovies (optional), capers and olive oil.
Salt and pepper the chicken inside and out.
Toss the ingredients in the bowl together gently, and use to stuff the chicken.
Don't stuff too tightly.
Bake at 375° for 70 to 80 minutes.
Quarter, and serve the bird with the dressing.

title: venison burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into thick patties.
Cook on barbecue grill, 4 inches from coals or broil in oven for 10 minutes on each side (less for rare burgers).
Serve immediately in hot burger buns.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: confetti potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt oleo over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimiento, pepper and 1/2 cup of the cracker crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mary kay's company green beans
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute onions and mushrooms until onions are soft.
Season with garlic salt.
Drain beans well.
Add onion and mushroom mixture.

title: potato salad
directions: Do not overcook potatoes.
In large bowl mix mayonnaise, vinegar,
salt,
sugar,
pepper
and mustard until smooth.	Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pizza rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion.
Add tomato sauce or stewed tomatoes, garlic powder, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano and parsley flakes.
Combine cottage cheese with cooked rice.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Layer 1/3 rice mixture, 1/3 meat mixture and 1/3 cheese mixture until used up.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese. Serves 6.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: In a large pot, toss leeks (and onions, if used) in butter until soft.
Add chicken stock and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for approximately 15 minutes (with lid on).
Check frequently and if necessary, skim froth off with a spoon.
Season as desired.
Add water as necessary.
Serve with warm, crusty bread.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan. When cake is done, take a drinking straw and punch holes in the top of the cake while it is still hot and let cool.
Pour the can of crushed pineapple and juice all over the top of the cake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cool, add undrained strawberries and diced bananas.
When cooled to room temperature, turn 1/3 mixture into container and chill until firm.
Spread with Cool Whip and place remaining mixture on top.
Chill until firm, then serve.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix dressing and water together (dressing and water may be kept in container in refrigerator to be used again and again). Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine meat, onion, gravy and seasonings.
Place in buttered casserole dish and cover with mashed potatoes.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are slightly browned.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and bones and flake well.
Add all other ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Blend well and shape into log.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot grape cider
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat grape juice, apple cider, cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves, just to boiling, over high heat. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream margarine.
Add beaten egg, raisins, grated carrots and vanilla essence; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in grape juice last and mix well.
Pour into greased, floured pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: salad dressing cake(good to make when you're out of eggs.)
directions: Mix
together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Then add Miracle Whip, water and vanilla, mix well. Pour into 9x13 pan or 2 layer pans. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: toast
directions: This is a recipe for all of you kids out there, whose parents leave you on a Saturday morning with no food in sight.
Here's a quick and easy warm breakfast you can make yourself.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour and seasoning and pound mixture thoroughly into both sides of beef.
Cut into serving pieces.
Heat skillet and add fat.
Brown steaks well.
Mix vegetables and place over meat. Cover.
Cook over low heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Thicken remaining sauce for gravy.
Serves 6.

title: no cook strawberry jam
directions: Crush berries and measure.
Stir sugar into berries, mixing thoroughly.
Add pectin with water in a saucepan and bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir into berries immediately and continue to stir for 3 minutes.
A few sugar crystals will remain.
Quickly put mixture into jars and cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature until jam is set. Wait about 24 hours and put in freezer.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Wash chicken and dry well.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Roll chicken in this mixture and coat evenly.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, slowly heat oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and saute on both sides until brown, 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add garlic, thyme, basil and parsley to pan. Saute herbs, stirring over medium heat 5 minutes.
If using fresh tomatoes, scald in boiling water, peel and cut in quarters or add can with liquid.
Add tomato paste, sugar, Tabasco and 1 cup wine. Stir well.
Place chicken in sauce; bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into electric mixer. Churn.

title: oatmeal yeast rolls
directions: Combine oats, butter, brown sugar and salt in a very large mixing bowl.
Pour hot water over this, mixing slightly.
Let cool to room temperature, then stir in yeast dissolved in water.
Stir in enough flour to make a very stiff batter.
Knead about 5 minutes and then put this into approximately 3 dozen rolls and dip in melted butter.
Set in a warm place and let rise again until double in size and then bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until light brown in color.

title: corn beef dip no. 1
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Let chill before serving.
For best results, make the day before.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.
Serve in hollowed out bread, wheat crackers, chips.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin in
greased casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Top with corn, sliced carrots and onion thin over top.
Sprinkle bell pepper over crumbled, uncooked ground beef on top.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients well. Chill for 1 hour. Roll into 13 x 8 rectangle. Divide into 4 parts. Spread 1/3 cup preserves on each. Roll up and seal ends. Put onto ungreased cookie sheet. Cut 3 or 4 slits on each top. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Spread with xxx sugar.

title: messy chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Salt, pepper and flour as if you were going to fry.
Layer chicken in baking dish.
Pour soup (prepare soup according to directions on can) and soy sauce over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until tender.

title: beefed up broccoli
directions: Brown beef, onion, chili powder and salt.
Drain.
Add rice, broccoli and soups.
Mix well and put in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix all ingredients until crumbly.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Spread 1 can cherry pie filling. Put remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice). Mix flour, sugar and juice in saucepan. Cook until thickened. Cool. Whip eggs in a cup. Add vinegar, then add to flour mixture and cook until thickened. When cool, add Cool Whip and pineapple; mix. Add diced apples and chopped peanuts; mix well. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sticky barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Coat cooked meat at 275° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple muffins
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and orange peel.
Set aside.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Beat together corn oil, sugar and eggs until well combined. In a bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add to egg-sugar mixture, mixing well.

title: fruit cookie pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together butter and sugars until light and creamy. Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually blend into butter mixture until just moistened. Press dough evenly into 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove and cool. Spread with pudding, leaving 1-inch all around. Arrange fruit on pudding. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Reserve water and remove meat from bones.
Discard skin and bones.
Cook macaroni in reserved water. Drain mushrooms and olives; retain liquid.
Thicken liquid with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Cook.
Add mushrooms.
Brown onions in small amount of oil.
Add with tomato sauce to olive and mushroom sauce, seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain macaroni. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking pan in layers of macaroni mixed with the chicken, sauce and macaroni mix, remainder of sauce.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven or melted.

title: baked trout
directions: You will need aluminum foil (4 pieces large enough to roll up around trout).

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt and egg with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Then pour over all the butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine first two ingredients, cook 15 minutes and let cool. Add soda, sugar, flour, lard and salt to raisin mixture.
Mix together well, then add egg and vanilla to mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon in small bowl.
Swirl into batter with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, brown sugar, vanilla and milk in large bowl.
Using mixer, beat at medium speed until creamy. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar.
Stir in flour.
Stir in milk.
Add beaten eggs and baking powder.
Stir in corn.
Bake in buttered casserole for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown around edges.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add lemon rind and lemonade concentrate.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients, blending well. Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Gently fold them into batter.
Pour mixture into a well-buttered and lightly floured square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Dust top with powdered sugar or top with lemon flavored whipped cream.

title: orange salad
directions: Let all jell, then add topping.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Shape crescent rolls on pizza pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread on baked crust.
Put veggies on top of white mixture and chill overnight. Put cheese on top.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce head.

title: scott's sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Drain off the grease.
Put the hamburger back on the burner on low heat.
Add catsup until it looks like Sloppy Joes should look.
Add some dried onion and garlic powder. (If you're trying to impress someone, you can add some oregano.) Heat until it bubbles.
Serve on buns with pickles and potato chips.

title: apple sponge cake
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and pour in melted butter. Combine apples, sugar, lemon juice and corn syrup, mixing well. Transfer to buttered casserole.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add brown sugar and flour, beating well.
Add vanilla, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cover apples with batter and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Good with heavy cream or soft vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix well and pour over the top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Put sliced pound cake in dish layered with raspberries.
Leave overnight.
Put cream on top.
Then put raspberries on very top. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt chips and margarine.
Blend in sugar, eggs, nuts and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Cook the sausage until done and lay on paper towels to remove excess fat.
(Links can also be used.)
Mix the other ingredients together and put in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Cover ball with mixture of cream cheese softened with 2 tablespoons of milk. Great with wheat crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and add milk until consistency that batter will drop off spoon.
Drop into hot shortening to fry.

title: chicken oriental broccoli
directions: In skillet, heat oil and add 1/2 chicken and cook until all brown.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and pour into a well-buttered casserole dish. Bake in moderate (300° to 325°) oven for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Add all dry ingredients in 1 bowl.
Add all other ingredients in another bowl; add to dry ingredients and mix well.
(Dough may be a little moist.)
Roll cookie dough into small balls, then roll in either sugar or colored sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; bake until half done.
Place 1 kiss on top and press down a little. Finish baking until done or you see cookies are brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown hamburger, drain.
Simmer Ragu with hamburger and garlic powder.
Cook noodles.
Layer 3 times: noodles, sauce, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese (sliced).
Bake about 1 hour or until hot.
Put layer of Mozzarella on just before serving.

title: mom's hot bacon dressing
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Cook until brown and crisp.
Set aside.
Add together milk, sugar, flour, egg, vinegar and water. Cook until thick, then add bacon and fat.

title: chantilly mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Halve lengthwise and cool until can be handled. Scoop out potatoes into bowl. Spread in a shallow 3-quart gratin dish.
Increase oven temperature to 500°. Whip the cream to soft peaks and fold in Swiss cheese. Spread cream mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake approximately 10 minutes until top is browned.
Serves 6.

title: crab dip
directions: Saute onion and
bell
pepper in butter; stir in flour. Add soups slowly; add
rest
of
ingredients.
Can
be kept in crock-pot on low for serving.

title: easy serve baked ham
directions: Place ham on rack in shallow pan.
Spread preserves on top. Stud with whole cloves.
Heat in oven at 325° for 15 minutes per pound.
Baste with pan juices 3 to 4 times while baking.
Place on platter and cut string to serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Better if allowed to stand a while before serving.

title: easy pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix sour cream and pineapple, including juice.
Add pudding mix and mix with a spoon.
Pour into prepared crust and refrigerate.
When set, top with Cool Whip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Cook on low heat until meat is thoroughly cooked. Serve over hamburger buns.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken with potato stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add mashed potatoes.
Stir in eggs, stuffing, parsley, salt and pepper.
Turn into a greased shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top. Brush chicken with melted oleo; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour or until chicken is tender and browned.

title: louisiana banana cake
directions: *With butter or oleo, use 1/2 cup minus 2 tablespoons sour milk.
With vegetable shortening, use 1/2 cup sour milk.

title: grits casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 300° to 350° just until set.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onions in large skillet.
Drain off fat as it accumulates.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Place 1/2 cup hamburger mixture on bun. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix water with jello.
Put in cranberry sauce and stir.
Add sherbet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves about 30.
Easy, pretty and good!

title: crumb cake
directions: Blend together cake mix, eggs, milk and oil for 4 minutes. Pour in greased 11 x 15-inch or 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at least 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Spread shredded lettuce on bottom of 4-quart glass dish. Layer scallions, water chestnuts and frozen peas. Spread mayonnaise over top. Mix sugar, Parmesan, salt and garlic powder. Sprinkle on top.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours. Before serving, chop eggs and crumble bacon.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch enamel pan; let stand and refrigerate until firm.

title: vienna bread
directions: Slice bread not all the way through.
Melt together butter, chopped
onion, dry mustard, lemon juice, Lawry's seasoned salt and poppy seed.

title: breast of chicken
directions: Spread a thin layer of the chipped beef on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Roll chicken breasts into rounds and arrange in single layer in casserole.
Place 1/2 strip of bacon atop each breast.
Mix the sour cream with the soup.
Spread this sauce over the chicken breasts and cook in a 250° oven (uncovered) for 3 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well and add liquids. Mix, but do not use a mixer.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut slice off top of each potato.
Scoop out centers.
Leave 1/2-inch potato around walls.
Mash potatoes.
Stir in corned beef and butter. Add salt and pepper.
Divide mixture among potatoes; reheat.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Pan fry onions in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Add hamburger. Combine meat seasonings, noodles and soup in a 3-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large mixer bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute. Stir in baking mix, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cut into bars, 2 x 1-inch. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until well blended. Add egg; beat until light and lemon-colored.
With mixer running at low speed, add flour mixture alternately with banana mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.

title: dieters drink
directions: Mix dry milk and malted milk.
Add corn oil; work together until well mixed.
Add 4 cups ice water.
Process in blender until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Shake well before using.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Then add softened margarine until creamed together.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler or microwave.
Add rest of ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: hawaiian short ribs
directions: Toast sesame seed over medium-high heat until lightly browned in a 2 to 3-quart ovenproof pan; shake pan often to make it even. Remove from heat and arrange onion and meat on top of seed. Combine water, soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic, ginger, pepper and chili pepper over meat.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Stir well occasionally.
Remove meat and thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Make sure there is liquid on the meat at all times.

title: snack
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: raised donuts
directions: Mix water, buttermilk, yeast and sugar together.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add oil and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt together. Add half flour and beat well, then add rest of flour.
Mix well with spoon.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Tip out on floured board and cut.
Let raise about 15 minutes.
Fry in hot grease at 375°.
Roll in sugar before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: goodnight kisses(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat 3 egg whites.
Add a dash of salt. Gradually add sugar and beat until very stiff peaks.
Add a few drops of food coloring of your choice.
Fold in 2 packages of mint chocolate chips.
Place on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Turn oven off and put cookies in oven.
Let stay there until morning.
They are now ready to eat.

title: tuna chip spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Makes about 3 2/3 cups.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix dough.
Knead slightly and roll to about 1/2 inch thick. Keep sausage at room temperature for 1 hour.
Break into small pieces and cover dough.
Roll side to center and then other side and roll until they meet in the middle.
Cut down center with sharp knife.
Separate and fasten ends to make 2 rolls. Refrigerate until chilled.
Put on cutting board and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: autumn caramel cheesecake
directions: Saute apples for 5 minutes.
Beat cream cheese.
Add nutmeg and sugar; stir well.
Then add eggs and everything else.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is firm.
Chill for 4 hours. Serve with hot caramel topping.

title: mock sour cream raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk and yogurt. Add the pudding mix; cook and stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens. Stir in allspice. Add raisins; mix well. Let cool for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour into pastry shell. Chill at least 2 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: ann's florida lobster tails
directions: In a large pot, boil lobster tails in boiling water.
Do not cook all the way.
Split tails in half.
Remove meat.
Powder tails with flour, salt and pepper.

title: tortilla chip soup
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in large pot and simmer for 30 minutes minimum.
Place crushed chips in bowls, add soup and sprinkle cheese on top.
Other garnishes:
sour cream, avocado slices

title: ham and fresh vegetable medley(30 minute skillet)
directions: With sharp knife, cut boneless ham into 1/4-inch thick strips, about 3-inches long.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Cut green and red peppers into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Cut onion, yellow squash and zucchini into 1/4-inch wide slices.

title: maw-maw's sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add soda.
Add flour one cup at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add sour cream; beat well.
Add egg whites; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour until top is golden brown.

title: extra special coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Cream the margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs, then stir in flour and milk alternately.
Pour into 8-inch greased and floured pans (will fill 3).
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and put it in a greased casserole dish. Cook broccoli and drain. Stir into broccoli the Cheez Whiz, soup and onions. Pour broccoli mixture over rice. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Chicken, turkey or ham can be added.

title: colombian huevos rancheros
directions: Take a large 12-inch cast-iron skillet.
Put in olive oil. Saute the onions.
Remove from pan.
Layer onions and tomatoes back into pan in alternate layers.
(Reserve enough to make 1 final layer.)
Arrange the steaks on these layers, topping the steaks with the remaining onions and tomatoes.
Bake this at 350° until the meat is done to degree desired.
Remove skillet from oven to medium-hot stove.
Break one egg onto each steak.
When the eggs are cooked, serve as dinner or brunch.

title: mashed potatoes with chives
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan.
Add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until very tender; drain.

title: crab spread
directions: Arrange layers on platter and chill overnight.
For first layer, combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise and garlic salt with electric mixer until creamy; spread on platter.
Spread chili sauce for second layer.
For third layer, sprinkle on crab meat.
Garnish with parsley for the fourth layer.

title: mock lasagne casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, pepper, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine and drain. Place in warm dish.
Add remaining ingredients. Toss and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and caraway seed in a large bowl.
Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add up to 3/4 cup buttermilk to make a soft, but not sticky dough.
Add raisins.
Knead dough until smooth, about 1 minute.
Shape into a 5-inch disc and put in a baking pan.
Cut a 1/4-inch deep cross in the top.
Brush top with milk.
Bake until golden, about 35 minutes.

title: pecan praline cookies
directions: Add vanilla to egg white;
then sugar and pecans dusted in flour
to
the egg white.
Mix well until pecans are coated with sugar
and	egg
white
mixture.
Drop
to	spoonfuls on well-greased
cookie
sheet.
Drop far apart so cookies do not stick to
each
other
when baking.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Thaw berries and blend smooth in food processor or blender.
In large bowl, mix together pineapple, banana, yogurt and nuts.
Add strawberries and sugar.
Spoon into 12 paper lined muffin cups. Freeze.
When frozen, remove from muffin pan and place in freezer bag, if desired.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Makes 12.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter 2 (9-inch) pans.
Combine all ingredients together; mix with wooden spoon.
Pour into pans; bake at 325° until set, about 40 to 45 minutes.
This pie makes its own crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip, or Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix twice.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: savory rice pilaf
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Cook rice over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Let stand, uncovered, for 5 minutes; fluff with a fork.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Heat oil and syrup until warm and blended. Pour over pecans and mix lightly to coat.
Roast in a 300° oven for one hour.
Stir frequently.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cottage cheese, butter, salt and eggs. Stir in Jiffy mix.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and bacon bits.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or more until done (test with toothpick).
Cool and remove from pan.

title: farmer's-style chops(makes 6 servings)
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Coat with 2 tablespoon of flour. In a large skillet over medium heat, brown chops in oil. In slow cooker, place potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle remaining flour over and toss to coat.
Layer over potatoes (in order), cabbage, salt, pepper, pork chops, bouillon granules, 1/4 cup water and stewed tomatoes with juice.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook until vegetables and pork chops are tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Let stand 10 minutes. Whip the cream until stiffened. Fold into mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Mash shrimp with fork and add to mixture.
Store overnight in refrigerator for flavors to blend.
Remove one hour before serving.

title: oven stew
directions: Bake at 300° in covered baking dish for 3 hours.
Serve on buttered noodles or rice.

title: jezebel jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Delicious with ham or fowl.
Very good as a cocktail dip for thin slices of rare tenderloin.

title: carrot cake with buttermilk glaze
directions: Mix dry ingredients
and set aside.
Beat eggs one at a time. Beat in
sugar,
oil,
buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, carrots, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pineapple cheese roll
directions: In medium bowl, with fork beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in pineapple, half of the pecans, pepper, onion and salt.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 to 40 minutes.
Shape into ball; roll in the remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: fresh pear cake(apples can be used instead of pears.)
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and egg together.
Add the next 9 ingredients and mix well.
Add pears and mix.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased pan (I use a Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Saute vegetables in the oil. Add the roux mix slowly. Stir constantly and begin to add broth. Add sausage and remainder of broth; cook slowly. Add the black pepper, cayenne pepper, thyme, bay leaf and rosemary. Cook over low heat for 30 minutes in heavy Dutch oven. Add more water if needed. Add the file gumbo powder and cook 10 minutes or let stand. Serve over hot rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth. Heat margarine in a baking dish or pan.
When hot, add batter. Pour rhubarb on top of batter.
Bake at 350° or 400° about 30 to 35 minutes, until brown on top.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Cook cobs 1/2 hour, strain through wet cloth.
Use 3 cups juice.
Add Sure-Jell to boiling juice.
Add sugar and boil 4 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil water and cook pasta as directed on package. Rinse chicken and pat
dry.
In a large skillet, cook cut up chicken (1 to 1
1/2-inch
pieces)
in
hot
oil over medium-high heat until chicken is	no
longer
pink,
about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove
chicken
from
pan.
Keep
warm.
Heat butter in skillet.	Cook garlic and mushrooms over medium heat until browned slightly,
about
2 minutes. Stir in soup, light cream and Parmesan	cheese.
Add
cooked
chicken
and
cook 1 minute. Serve over drained pasta or toss together.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to a full boil and then boil one minute.
Stir mixture continuously.
Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter, vanilla, oats and if desired the coconut.
Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper and let cool.
Makes 40.

title: "easy roast"
directions: Wash roast
and
place in large boiler; fill to the top with water.
Add salt, pepper and onion soup.
Turn your stove on low heat and cook for 4 to 5 hours.
Fifteen minutes before you are ready
to
serve,
add
mushroom
soup and one can of water; mix well and let simmer.
Serve hot.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Add soda to vinegar and set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food color.
Add the paste mixture to the creamed mixture and mix together well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add soda and vinegar; mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into thin cookies and place in pizza pan. Bake according to cookie dough directions.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Beat egg yolk, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Beat vigorously.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream, pound cake or angel food cake.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Bake at 350 degrees. Do not brown. If cookies try to break, use a little more flour.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix first three ingredients.
Stir mixture with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Stir vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine melted butter and garlic.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from pan.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Butter 10 x 14-inch casserole.
Line with tortillas.
Mix. Layer chili, beans with juice and cover with cheese.
Layer 6 tortillas.
Mix tomatoes and soup.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: yummy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease two cookie sheets. In a large bowl, cream together margarine, peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar until smooth. Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla and almond extracts. Combine flour, soda and salt; stir into the peanut butter mixture. Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place them 2 inches apart onto the cookie sheets. Use a wet fork, dipped in sugar to make the crisscross pattern on top. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in preheated oven. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely. Grab a glass of milk and enjoy.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Beat eggs with milk. Dip the eggplant in milk, then
in cracker crumbs.
Fry in Crisco and oleo, (half and half)
until nicely browned.
Do not fry too fast.

title: sweet and sour black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix altogether.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to heat or serve cold.
Best if prepared 24 hours in advance.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops.
Coat with flour.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in a baking dish.
Add rice, green pepper, onion, tomato sauce and water.
Bake at 350° until rice and chops are done.

title: hershey's light cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch round pans with cooking spray.
In a bowl combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In saucepan, melt corn oil spread.
Stir in sugar.
Remove from heat. Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients and whisk until well blended.
Pour into pans. Bake 20 minutes or until the layers test clean with a toothpick.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping cobs to get the "milk." Place in skillet; add water, butter and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes or until tender. Salt to taste.

title: fruit and cheese sparkle
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup of the measured liquid and chill until thickened.
Add pineapple.
Pour gelatin mixture into mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Meanwhile, dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add remaining measured liquid and the lemon juice. Gradually blend into softened cheese, beating until smooth.
Chill until thickened.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spoon into mold over clear layer.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish with pineapple slices, cherries and mint leaves, if desired. Makes about 5 or 10 servings.

title: chinese no-bake cookies
directions: Melt all chips until smooth, stirring occasionally, over low heat in a double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: weight watchers pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin, carrots and raisins.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared muffin pan, sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: plan ahead mashed potatoes(will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks)
directions: Mash until light and fluffy.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat in oven before serving.

title: fish bait
directions: Add 1/2 cup cornmeal and 1/2 cup flour to strawberry-banana jello while the jello liquid is boiling.
Let the mixture cool to lukewarm and then add the remaining 1/2 cup cornmeal and 1/2 cup flour.
When mixture is at room temperature, the concoction can be rolled into small balls.

title: tuna corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in medium saucepan over medium-high heat until brown and crisp, turning once. Drain on paper towels, reserving drippings in saucepan. Add onion and celery to pan drippings; cook and stir over medium-high heat for 3 minutes or until onions are tender. Add flour, stirring until well blended; cook 1 minute. Stir in milk, thyme, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently until thickened. Stir in corn and tuna; cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until corn is tender, stirring frequently. Crumble bacon. Serve chowder sprinkled with bacon.

title: un-fried chicken breading
directions: Toss all ingredients into a large, tightly sealing plastic bag.
Seal and shake well to mix.

title: rice pudding
