directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and continue cooking for 30 to 45 minutes until rice is soft and mixture is creamy.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put the first four ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from stove and add the other four ingredients.
Stir together and spread in long cake pan.
Let cool and harden.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Mix chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels in microwave dish; heat on High for 1 minute.
Stir if needed.
Heat for 1 more minute.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Spoon out on cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: festive turkey salad
directions: Toss together; add dressing.
Pour on bed of romaine leaves. Add almonds; chill at least 1 hour.

title: turkey lasagne
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together the noodles, soup, milk, salt and poultry seasoning.
Heat through.
Mix together cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Add onion, green pepper and parsley.
Blend well.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients into ground beef and form into balls.

title: broccoli stir-fry
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli and coarsely chop stalks and flowerets.
Heat olive oil and dark sesame oil in a wok or a large nonstick skillet at medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, red pepper, onion and garlic; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Remove from wok.
Combine soy sauce and next 7 ingredients; stir well.
Add to wok and cook, stirring constantly, just until thickened.
Return broccoli mixture to wok, and stir-fry just until thoroughly heated and coated.
Stir in water chestnuts.
Sprinkle with pine nuts before serving.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese cake with apricot sauce
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie plate.
Using an electric mixer, blend cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla well.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread evenly over completely cooled cheese filling.
Bake 8 minutes at 475°.
Top should not brown.
Cool at room temperature.
Chill.
Blend cornstarch and sugar; add hot nectar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Cool.
When ready to serve, pour over individual servings of cheese cake.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large pan, place potatoes, broccoli, celery, carrots and onion in 2 quarts water.
Cook for about 20 minutes; do not drain. Add to the cooked vegetables the flour, milk and Cheez Whiz. Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.
Stir constantly.
This will make about 1 gallon of soup.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add with milk (alternately).
Add nuts and pour in greased pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Fill cookie press. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 9 minutes.
Serves 5 dozen.

title: sand dabs(pecan fingers)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt and vanilla and mix well. Add flour and nuts.
Chill.
Shape into small finger type rolls. Bake on buttered sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: voleano creamed potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Add milk, cream or margarine and baking powder.
Whip until light and smooth.
Pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: simple cinnamon rolls
directions: Let bread rise.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Pinch off bread and make the size of a walnut.
Melt butter and roll pinched bread in butter, then sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 8 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce, bacon, cauliflower pieces and onion in this order.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; spread on top.
Cover generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 8 hours.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: hamburger pizza pie
directions: Brown crumbled hamburger with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix Mozzarella cheese, crushed tomatoes and oregano in a small bowl. In a large, greased pie plate, place hamburger and pat well to spread evenly.
Spread cheese mixture over hamburger.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups. Combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, baking powder and salt.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cool and slice.
Saute bacon and onions (do not drain grease).
Add potatoes, chili powder and garlic.
Fry until potatoes are heated.
I use an iron skillet.

title: pork tenderloin with orange marmalade
directions: Make a cut lengthwise down the center about halfway through the pork tenderloin.
In a small bowl, mix together mustard, garlic, rosemary and black pepper.
Spread mixture along the cut surface of the tenderloin.
Reshape and tie in several places. Place on rack above roasting pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until internal temperature of meat reaches 160°. Mix together remaining orange marmalade and chicken stock in a small saucepan.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, until thickened.
Spoon sauce over tenderloin and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings, 160 calories, 3 grams of fat per serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let stand (refrigerate) several hours before serving.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes in center of oven at 375° or until brown.
Remove to cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground meat.
Line Tater Tots in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Don't stack them on top of each other.
Drain meat.
In a large bowl, mix soups and meat and then add 1/2 can of water.
Pour on top of Tater Tots.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and add grated cheese on top.
Cook for another 15 minutes.
Take out, cool and enjoy!

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, bouillon, red and black pepper.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk and corn.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in skillet.
Add scallops and mushrooms.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until scallops are done. Divide scallops and mushrooms into 4 shallow dishes or shells.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain grease. Add Cheddar soup and mix together.
Place meat mixture in baking dish (2-quart size dish).
Top with Velveeta cheese in thin layer. Remove crescent rolls from can; do not unroll. Cut into 1/4-inch circles.
Place rolls on top of meat and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown.
Serves 6.

title: cherry nut bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat just until blended after each addition.
Fold in nuts and cherries. Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.

title: buns
directions: Mix together.
Let rise twice. Very good for cinnamon rolls.

title: bill's beef stew
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Combine meat, flour and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Brown meat in bacon fat; stir often.
Add oil if needed.
Add onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, broth, wine and thyme.
Cover and cook slowly, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes; cook until vegetables are done.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: deviled green beans
directions: Drain liquid from beans into a saucepan and cook down to about half.
Add butter, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add beans.
Heat and serve.

title: grandma elliott's butterscotch and coconut cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; cream oleo and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in butterscotch chips and nuts; mix well.
Then chill a few hours.
Drop by teaspoon into coconut. Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top with a cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: coleslaw supreme
directions: Place oil, onion, sugar, vinegar, poppy seeds, celery seeds, salt, and hot pepper sauce in a blender container.
Cover and blend until uniform.
Combine green and red cabbage, raisins, and almonds in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss until all ingredients are well coated.
Chill up to 1 hour and serve.

title: crockpot macaroni and cheese
directions: Spray crock pot with cooking spray.
Add to crock pot both milks, eggs and melted margarine.

title: butter cookies
directions: Soften butter, then add to mixture of sugar and vanilla.
Mix together, then add flour.
Knead the dough, then roll it out on the countertop with a rolling pin.
Make dough into little balls and flatten into cookies.
Bake at 310° for about 25 minutes.

title: mixed nut bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix together flour, brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken upside-down cornbread
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Add onion and celery.
Saute until limp.
Add cornstarch and blend.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add salt and broth.
Cook, stirring over low heat, until thickened and bubbling. Cover and set aside.
In buttered 8 1/2-inch square pan arrange sliced olives and chicken.
Spoon thickened broth over chicken.

title: homemade bread or rolls
directions: Place milk, hot water, yeast, salt, sugar, shortening and 4 1/2 cups flour in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add 2 eggs; beat really well.
Add remaining 5 1/2 cups flour; mix by hand.
Dump out on floured board; knead until smooth.
Let raise until double in size; knead again and form into loaves or rolls. Bake rolls at 375° for 30 minutes; bread at 350° for 45 minutes. Butter tops while still hot.
Makes 3 loaves or 3 to 4 dozen rolls.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, butter and confectioners sugar until smooth. Spread this into square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir remaining ingredients into eggs.
Spread over top of baked pastry. Bake another 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: pot roasted duck(modern)
directions: Chop onions and green pepper.
Stuff cavities with onions and peppers.
Season duck with salt and chili powder.
Wrap bacon around ducks.
Heat grease in a heavy pot; add ducks.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Add small amounts of water to prevent burning during cooking.

title: lemon glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, 7-Up and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover; Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Drain reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Place carrots in a serving bowl and keep warm.
Return reserved liquid to saucepan; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Pour over carrots and serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla on high speed until frothy. Pour into chilled can.
Add half and half, whipping cream and milk to fill line.
Prepare per your ice cream maker instructions.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries (frozen); stir, then cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Mix in the Dream Whip.
Tear up the cake in bite size pieces; spread 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over cake. Repeat with rest of mixture, then cake.
Refrigerate; let set at least 4 or 5 hours.
This can also be frozen.

title: impossible chicken n' broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray deep dish pie plate with Pam.
Rinse broccoli under cold running water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese, chicken, onion and mushrooms in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds) in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix with hands.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out and put on crumbs.
Return to oven for 15 minutes more.
Cool and sprinkle with confectionary sugar.

title: basic finger paint
directions: Put soap flakes in medium sized bowl.
Gradually add water. Beat with rotary or electric beater to a soft, smooth consistency that holds a peak.
Color if desired.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with 2/3 cup sugar.
Add flour mixture with milk, stirring just enough to blend.
Add 3 tablespoons cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into 8-inch square pan.
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over batter; do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour.
Pudding will separate into cake and sauce.
Cool slightly in pan.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat 1 minute after each egg is added.
Pour in 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes until brown and set.

title: tiramisu
directions: Prepare mascarpone mixture by combine 3 egg yolks, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 Tbsp. espresso or coffee, 2 Tbsp. brandy into a large mixing bowl.
Beat with rotary beater or mixer for 2 to 3 minutes. Add mascarpone and continue to beat for another 3 to 5 minutes, until consistency is smooth.
Set aside.

title: christmas drink
directions: Make this while raspberries are in season.
Do not use until Christmas holidays.
Mix vodka and sugar.
Add raspberries.
Cover container, but not tight.
Keep cool or refrigerate.
To serve: Mix with 7-Up, half and half for strong drink.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can water.
Sprinkle onion soup on steak. Pour mushroom soup over steak.
Cook in crock-pot on medium heat all day.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop all in food processor.
Add sugar.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes.
Will keep several weeks and can be frozen.

title: banana bran loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in margarine until coarse like cornmeal.
Add bananas, eggs, milk, dates and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Eat plain or frost with caramel icing.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until tender, rinse and let cool until you are able to hold them in your hand.
Cook meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients together except shells.
Stuff shells. Place in oven cooking dish.
Cover shells with your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 35 to 40 shells.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Combine butter and crackers; sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: real corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well in mixing bowl.
Melt in bread pan 1 tablespoon lard or shortening.
Pour sizzling grease into mixture. Pour into hot pan.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in microwave dish and cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Add stuffing to sausage and onion.
Add enough water to moisten stuffing.
After zucchini are cooked and cooled enough to handle, scoop out inside of zucchini and add to sausage mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place shells on baking dish and stuff with sausage mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: german slaw
directions: Layer slaw, onion and bell pepper in a large bowl. Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and salt in microwavable bowl. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes, almost to a boil, until sugar dissolves. Pour mixture over slaw. Refrigerate before serving and stir to marinate vegetables.

title: date roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook until syrup forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add dates.
Stirring frequently, cook until candy becomes very thick.
The bubbles will pop with a hissing sound and the mixture will follow the spoon around the pan. Take from heat and add nuts and coconut.
Stir until mixture has the consistency of soft cookie dough.
Turn candy on a wet cloth. Form a long roll and wrap in the wet cloth until cool.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place
ground beef in baking dish. Over the meat sprinkle layer of onions, 3 layers of potatoes, salt, pepper, cheese, pork and beans, and tomato soup. Cover tightly with foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: poblano mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat broiler. On foil-lined baking sheet, broil chiles, cut side down, 4-inches from heat, 10 minutes, turning sheet occasionally, until chiles are evenly charred. Transfer to paper bag; seal and let stand until cool. Remove skins; cut chiles into 1/4-inch dice. Set aside.

title: bacon and beef steak wrappers
directions: Roll ground chuck with rolling pin on waxed paper into a 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and cheese.
Combine chopped mushrooms, olives and green onions; sprinkle evenly on meat.
Roll meat (by gently lifting waxed paper), jelly roll style; freeze until firm enough to be sliced.
Cut into 6 pieces; wrap each piece with a slice of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick. Cook on the grill for 10 minutes on each side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes with corned beef
directions: Put oil in pan; add potatoes.
Cook until they are almost done.
Add corned beef, onion and tomato until everything is done.

title: summer pudding
directions: Bring fruit and sugar to a boil and simmer until barely tender.
Line a deep pudding bowl with slices of white bread and fill with the fruit.
Cover top with slices of bread.
Place a saucer on top of pudding to fit the basil.
Put a weight on the saucer to apply pressure.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach salad with bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain.
Mix diced bacon with Miracle Whip, water, vinegar and garlic.
Wash spinach and serve topped with fresh mushrooms and sliced hard-boiled egg.
Serve dressing on side or over spinach.

title: double toffee delight
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl.
Pour 1/3 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 brown sugar mixture.
Pour remaining batter over brown sugar mix and sprinkle remaining brown sugar mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: glaze for bundt cake
directions: Boil for 1 minute.
Put in pan of cold water and stir; it will turn white.
Dribble over cake.

title: hearty winter minestrone
directions: Shape sausage into 3/4-inch meatballs.
In saucepan, in hot oil, cook meatballs until browned.
Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Add broth, soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Add pasta.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes or until pasta is done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 6 cups.
Recipe may be doubled for more.

title: delicious peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and margarine and form into 1-inch balls.
Place on a big cookie sheet and chill for a few minutes. Melt chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip each peanut butter ball into chocolate.
Keep chocolate at low temperature while dipping.
These freeze well and are great right out of the freezer.

title: blueberry breakfast cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan and pour in batter.
Top with topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Place onion in 1 quart microproof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on HI for 2 minutes.
Spread out on paper towel to absorb excess moisture.
Place carrots in same casserole. Cover and cook on HI for 2 1/2 minutes.
Spread out on paper towel.
Repeat with mushrooms, cooking on HI for 2 1/2 minutes. In the same casserole, stir together Ricotta cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Spoon spaghetti sauce into 12 X 7 inch microproof baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients in layers as follows.
Form the first layer with 3 lasagna noodles, spinach, onions and half the Ricotta mixture.
Form the second layer with 3 lasagna noodles, carrots, mushrooms and remaining half of Ricotta mixture.
Top with tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Double-wrap casserole tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 6-12 hours. Remove casserole from refrigerator and let stand 1 hour.
Cook on HI for 8 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cook on 50 for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
8 serving.
Total cooking time:
35 minutes.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts, coconut and white chips.
Roll dough into 1 or 2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake for 9 to 15 minutes, depending on size of cookie.

title: beer cheese
directions: Cook on stove, low heat, until well blended.
Serve in hollowed out rye bread when cool.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat in skillet and season with onion salt, salt and pepper. Place hamburger, noodles and cheese in a greased casserole dish in layers. Pour tomato sauce mixed with water over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup together; cook 4 minutes.
Add peanuts; stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla; stir and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in soda and pour into buttered pan.
Cool for 1/2 to 1 hour and break into pieces.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix egg and milk together; add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel; pour in some of the batter, then remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into pan filled with 1-inch of hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Clean lettuce and arrange leaves on a platter.
Place pineapple in center.
Place shrimp around pineapple.
Place sliced cucumber around edge of platter.
Sprinkle dressing over top lightly.
Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together and place in pie shell; ready to eat.

title: closet cucumber pickles
directions: You will need a glass gallon jar.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter.
Mix sugar and rice cereal. Pour butter mix over cereal mix.
Blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm.

title: ethel's roux
directions: Mix cooking oil, chicken broth and flour.
Brown on top of stove; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic; add to flour mix.
Cut cooked chicken in blocks; add to mixture.
(Optional: Add cooked okra.)
Serve on top of cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cookie mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide into 6 plastic baggies and store. When ready for cookies, mix one bag with 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter flavored Crisco.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Each bag yields 18 to 24 cookies.

title: strawberry shortcake surprise
directions: Mix Eagle Brand condensed milk and softened cream cheese, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Tear cake into little pieces and layer the bottom of a deep bowl.
This is the first layer.
Layer 1 container of the strawberries over this.
Layer 1/2 of the milk/cheese mixture over the strawberries.
Begin again with the cake, other half of strawberries and milk/cheese mixture.
Chill for hours.

title: aunt alice's reception salad
directions: Fold into the cream cheese just before other mixture is ready to congeal.
Pour into greased mold (vegetable oil or Wesson oil). Refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: black walnut coconut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk; mix well.
Add crushed walnuts and coconut flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: dill pickle soup
directions: Combine and cook the first 5 ingredients, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add pickles; cook 15 minutes more.
Beat milk and flour until smooth; return to pot.
Boil soup until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg with sour cream.
Pour some hot soup into sour cream mixture; add to soup.
Do not boil soup after sour cream has been added, or sour cream will curdle.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in butter and season.
Saute onion and peppers. Mix soy sauce and flour until all the lumps have dissolved.
Pour soy sauce mixture in with meat and vegetables and stir well!
(You may need to add water.) Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Enjoy!

title: sopa
directions: Melt oleo and add chilies and onions until tender.
Add chicken, soup and chestnuts.
Tear tortillas in fourths and arrange part on greased casserole.
Top each layer with chicken and cheese. Make 2 layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients plus 15 crackers.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix remaining crackers and butter; pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Very good served with ham.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the corn and green beans and set aside.
Mix the soup, sour cream and onions together.
Add the corn and green beans to the soup mixture and put in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and bell pepper until tender. Spread in casserole and dot with butter. Combine soup and milk and pour over cabbage. Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot.

title: southwest stew
directions: Brown beef or turkey with onion.
Drain and add to meat the corn and pinto beans.
Add water, tomatoes, picante sauce, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Serve with shredded cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter dish.
Put in apples and water.
Mix together sugar, margarine, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Stir in sugar, vanilla, cocoa and chopped pecans.
Press into unbuttered pan.
Place a pecan half on each square.

title: scampi primavera
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook and stir garlic and lemon peel 30 seconds.
Add vegetables and shrimp and cook about 4 minutes over medium heat or until shrimp turn pink.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, lemon juice, basil and parsley; stir well.
Spoon over hot, cooked spaghetti and toss.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa in bowl.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs, water and vinegar; mix.

title: cream cheese swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare brownies as directed on package except spread only 2/3 of the dough in pan. Beat cream cheese and butter in small mixer bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spread over dough in pan.
Drop remaining dough by tablespoonfuls onto cream cheese mixture.
Swirl lightly with spatula for marbled effect.
Bake for 35 minutes. Cool before cutting into squares.

title: diet dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in electric blender.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serve with a tray of assorted fresh vegetables.

title: fruitcake midgets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar; beat well and add egg, lemon juice and vanilla.
Combine flour with remaining dry ingredients.
Add fruit mixture to creamed mixture; then add flour mixture and blend well.
Fill midget baking cups 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Store in tin boxes and freeze until ready to use.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and rice.
Add green pepper, tomato sauce, cumin seed and chili powder with 2 cans.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and mixture has thickened.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat in a crock-pot on low for 2 to 5 hours.

title: grilled salmon sandwich with hot mustard
directions: Combine mustard and sugar in small bowl.
Stir in 1 1/2 tablespoons water.
Add soy sauce and 1 teaspoon oil; set aside. Heat a grill or grill pan until very hot.
Brush salmon with remaining oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grill for 5 minutes or until browned.
Turn and cook for another 5 minutes.

title: judy's best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, eggs, oleo, syrup, Crisco and vanilla. Beat until creamy.

title: orange julius
directions: Add all ingredients to blender.
Mix until ice cubes are crushed.

title: broccoli with orange sauce
directions: Place broccoli and a small amount of water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 5 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Meanwhile in a small saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and bouillon.
Stir in water, orange juice and peel until blended.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes until thickened.
Drain broccoli and place in a serving bowl.
Garnish with orange slices and drizzle with sauce.

title: pork chop rice
directions: In large skillet, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil about 3 minutes.
Then turn down to simmer.
Cook, covered, until done, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tropical spritzers
directions: Combine club soda and guava juice.
Stir lightly.
Pour into glasses and garnish with strawberries.
Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, then add egg, water, oil and pumpkin.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased loaf pans, then cool.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix in flour to form dough.
Roll into small balls. Make hole in center with thumb on a baking sheet.
Put a teaspoon preserves in center.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium saucepan, bring water to a boil. Mix in instant rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. In 9 x 13 baking dish, mix prepared rice, chicken, soups, butter, milk, broccoli, onion and cheese. Bake in preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes until cheese is melted. Stir halfway through cooking time to evenly distribute cheese.

title: calorie watchers pasta with shrimp, scallops and vegetables
directions: Cook zucchini, peppers and onion in oil for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add parsley, clam juice, cream * and scallops.
Cook gently until scallops are tender.
Add shrimp and cook (1 to 2 minutes).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour or ladle over freshly cooked pasta.

title: low fat gravy
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion, mushrooms and parsley in 1/4 cup broth until tender. Combine cornstarch, pepper and 1/2 cup broth. stir until smooth. Add to the pan with remaining broth. Bring to boil, stirring. Boil two minutes. Yields 2 cups.

title: meat burritos
directions: Fry meat strips in oil in a skillet over medium heat until browned.
Add carrots, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute, then add tomatoes, green chilies, water and seasonings. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook until done. Warm tortillas.

title: cranberry souffle salad
directions: Mix together gelatine, sugar and salt.
Add hot water (boiling) and stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice and mix well with rotary beater.
Pour into pan and freeze in refrigerator 10 or 15 minutes until firm 1-inch from edge of pan.
Remove to chilled bowl and beat until fluffy.
Fold in cranberry, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into mold; set until firm.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple until all juice is off.
Mix ground cranberries, sugar and pineapple; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add grapes, nuts and marshmallows to cranberry mixture.
Whip cream stiff and fold in mixture.
Keep in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: lemony grilled chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter, thyme and pepper sauce in a small bowl.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper.
Place chicken bone side down on grill over hot coals.
Baste frequently with sauce.
Serve with remainder of sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: party quesadillas
directions: Blend together the first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Spread mixture over 5 tortillas, covering with the remaining tortillas.
Brush tops lightly with vegetable oil.
On a baking sheet, broil until golden (about 1 minute).
Turn, repeat process. Broil until cheese is melted.
Cut each into 8 wedges.

title: apple pie
directions: Lightly mix apples, sugars, flour, salt, nutmeg, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Put in pie shell, laying apples flat.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Slit top crust to allow steam to escape. Moisten edges of crust well with cold water.
With fingers or fork, pinch crusts together to make tight seal.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add molasses.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Combine soda, baking powder, salt, ginger and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat until smooth. Roll or pat into 6 greased 9-inch cake pans, about 3/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Cook rice according to box.
Mix broccoli, rice, cream of celery soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all together; put Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: custard
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out dry.

title: blue ribbon spaghetti sauce
directions: Peel and mash tomatoes.
Cook for 3 hours.
Add onions, hot peppers, oil, basil, oregano, sugar and salt.
Cook for 1 hour. Add tomato paste.
Bring to a hard boil.
Place in jars and process for 45 minutes in hot water bath or 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients on low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat; beat sugar in until smooth.
Drizzle over tube chocolate cake while cake is warm.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in ungreased 9 x 14 x 2-inch cake pan. Make 3 holes in mixture.
In one add vanilla, in second add vinegar, in third add cooking oil.
Pour 2 cups cold water over all and blend with a fork until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse well.
Add green pepper and onion to beans.
Mix other ingredients and add to bean mixture.
Mix well. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix with other ingredients and shape into small balls. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add all 4 items to pan in layers.
Bake about 40 minutes until done.

title: beef potato boats
directions: Brown beef, onion, green peppers and celery in a skillet. Drain fat.
Add seasoning and sauce.
Cut potatoes 1/2 lengthwise. Scoop out and reserve shells.
Mash potatoes and combine with meat mixture.
Fill shells and sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix dry and keep in airtight container.
Mix 2 heaping teaspoons in 1 cup hot water for cool evenings.
For cold symptoms, asthma or sinus conditions.
Will warm you up, soothe a sore throat and clear congested lung or nose.
And is full of vitamins and sunshine.

title: mandel toast (or mandel brot)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Then add vanilla.
Sift together and into egg mixture, flour, baking powder and salt. Beat gradually, adding nuts.
Grease cookie sheet.
Divide dough into 3 "loaves" on sheet (or use 2 sheets).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Slice diagonally while hot.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top.
Return to oven 5 to 8 minutes.
Keeps well and stays crisp if packed in tins.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix in brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add to oatmeal.
Mix in flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Put in greased and floured cake pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a casserole dish, then lay the chicken in the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy! Good with rice.

title: apricot pecan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add orange peel, pecans and apricots.
Mix with fingers to coat.
Beat apricot juice, orange juice and egg with wire whisk. Pour liquid into dry ingredients; do not overmix, just fold until blended.
Add margarine; mix. Spoon into buttered and floured loaf pans.
Place on table with thump to expel air bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides with knife and turn onto rack.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Grease square baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat candy coating in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended. Pour over cereal in large bowl; toss until cereal is well coated.
Press in pan.
Heat jelly and water in saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until jelly is melted.
Drizzle over mixture in pan. Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 24.

title: pineapple burgers
directions: Make 2 large flat patties of the hamburger.
Place a pineapple ring between the patties.
Seal edges of patties.
Bake, fry or grill.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup, mustard in small saucepan and simmer.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add butter and poppy seed.
Stir gently.

title: chocolate chip cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Pour in melted butter.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: You will need 24 (1 1/2-inch) paper bonbon cups.

title: green beans with dill
directions: In large saucepan, bring an inch of unsalted water to a boil. Add the green beans and cook, covered, for 6 or 7 minutes or until just tender.
Drain in a colander.
Rinse under cold running water to stop the cooking and drain again.
In the same saucepan, melt the margarine over moderate heat.
Return the beans to the pan and toss for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.
Add lemon juice, pepper and dill.
Toss again and serve.
Serves 4.

title: frosted creams
directions: Spread on an oblong baking sheet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Ice with powdered sugar frosting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry potatoes until done in a 10-inch skillet.
In separate skillet, fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Drain potatoes, then pour egg mixture over top of fried potatoes.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 8 or 10 minutes, until eggs are set.
Take from oven. Place shredded cheese over egg-potato mixture.
Add bacon to top of casserole.
Place in oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted. Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli cauliflower raisin salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Mix broccoli, cauliflower, onion, sunflower seeds, raisins and bacon bits.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan. Add brown sugar and mix together thoroughly. Heat to boiling, then cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove pan from heat and add miniature marshmallows. Stir until they are melted and mixture is smooth. Put 2 cups sifted powdered sugar into mixing bowl. Add cooked mixture and vanilla; mix for 30 seconds on low speed, then beat until smooth and creamy. Ice cake while frosting is still a little warm. Makes enough to frost 2 layer cakes or a 9 x 13 pan cake.

title: classic ratatouille
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer in covered pot for 1 hour. Uncover and cook until thick.

title: easter egg rolls
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Cut the dough into 16 equal pieces. With the palm of your hand, flatten each piece into a 3-inch square.
Place a few raisins or jelly beans in the center; bring up the dough edges around the filling and pinch them together, forming an egg shape.
Place pinched side down on cookie sheet. Brush the rolls with the egg.
Cover with plastic wrap; put in a warm place and let rise until double in size.
Sprinkle tops of the rolls with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Add 1/2 cup sugar (reserve remaining 1/2 cup sugar), cloves, cinnamon and lemon juice, mixing well.
Pour into
buttered casserole.
Then mix the flour, remaining 1/2 cup sugar, oatmeal and butter to crumbly consistency in a separate bowl.
Add nuts, then sprinkle mixture over apple mixture in casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until apples are tender and crust browned.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream while hot.

title: tomato and white bean soup
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in olive oil. Add Italian seasoning and white wine. Add tomatoes and chicken broth. Simmer for 10 minutes. Add beans and salt and pepper.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Wash and pat dry rabbits.
Cut rabbits into quarters.
Salt and pepper rabbits.
Dust with flour and brown in oil.
Reduce heat to low.
Add water and simmer 45 minutes or until rabbit is tender.
Thicken liquid in pan and serve over cooked rice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute ground beef and onions in a small amount of fat in cooking pan or a chafing dish until meat is well browned.
Stir in condensed soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, over direct heat of chafing dish until thoroughly heated.

title: honey-poppy seed salad dressing
directions: In blender or with electric mixer, blend together all ingredients except the oil.
Gradually add oil, beating constantly, until mixture thickens.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 cups.
Approximate calories/serving:
1 tablespoon = 95.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all but Fritos together.
Add Fritos just prior to serving.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Combine cornmeal and flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend in enough milk to make soft dough.
Put onto floured board and knead gently 30 seconds. Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out with 2-inch biscuit cutter or sharp knife.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick; gradually add sugar and blend well. Add oil and beat.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: punch for big affairs
directions: Make syrup by boiling together sugar and 2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Add tea and juices.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Strain if desired.
Add cherries and their juice, 3 gallons water and ginger ale.
Pour over block of ice in punch bowl or over ice cubes. Serves 75.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Grease a cookie sheet with shortening.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 70 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple betty
directions: Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Place 1/3 of mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon rind.
Toss together until apples are well coated with sugar mixture.
Spoon 1/2 of apples over bread crumbs in casserole. Layer with more bread crumbs and apples, reserving 1/3 of crumbs for top.
Pour 1/4 cup of water over.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and brown for 5 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.

title: marty's infamous cornbread
directions: Mix together soda, salt, cornmeal, flour, jalapenos, eggs, buttermilk and heated bacon grease.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a skillet or pan.
Top with Mexicorn and 3/4 pound Cheddar cheese. Layer on remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with remaining cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: 30 minute chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook chicken and green pepper in hot oil until well browned, about 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, wine and 1/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water. Add strawberries; let cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts to Jell-O mixture.
Spread about half of Jell-O mixture in bottom of dish.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Spread sour cream over gelatin mixture, then layer remaining gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: chicken tortellini casserole
directions: Cook tortellini 5 minutes less than package directions indicate, as liquid will be absorbed from this recipe.
Drain well and place in bottom of lightly greased 8 1/2x11-inch casserole dish.
Grate 4 oz cheese and spread over pasta.
Cut chicken breasts into small cubes and roll in flour.
Brown in margarine. Remove chicken from pan and cook onions in same pan until transparent.
Add bouillon, chicken broth, sugar and mushrooms. Bring to a slow boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining 4 oz of cheese and continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Place the chicken pieces over the tortellini in the pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 300 degrees.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated. Serves 6-8.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
In large mixer bowl combine all ingredients except flour and raisins.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
Add flour; continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, stir in raisins.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: donna's delightful clam dip
directions: Mix clams, breadcrumbs, spices and butter all together with the juice of clams and place in a pie pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with Doritos or crackers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Separate into two balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in foil and chill.
Serve with chips and dips.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef in 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake until golden brown at 400°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl, mix well. Pour in buttered casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or knife comes out clean.

title: florence darby osgood's prune cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and cream.
Add dry ingredients, prunes and juice.
Bake in two layers in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost tops of layers with whipped cream.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute.
Add soup and cheese.
Add broccoli; stir.
Makes a large bowl of dip.

title: fruit punch
directions: Freeze ice in any desired shape and place in bottom of punch bowl, then pour chilled juices over ice. Add broken up sherbet just before ready to serve. Serves about 30.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well. Stir 1 tablespoon into a cup of hot water (or to taste).

title: raw apple-date cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cube.
Add rest of ingredients and heat in oven until warm, not hot.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Coat beef in flour mixture. Brown beef in oil until well browned on all sides.
Add onions, mushroom pieces, paprika and beef broth.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Shortly before serving, add sour cream to meat mixture and cook over low heat until heated through; stir constantly.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Into 2 1/2 cups hot applesauce, stir the soda.
Cool, then add pineapple and stir.
Mix all remaining ingredients; stir into the applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in large tube pan, which has been well-greased and lined with brown paper (grease both sides of paper).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; turn oven back to 275° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.

title: easy cherry tarts
directions: Divide pie filling among the crust.
Top with whipped topping and chocolate sprinkles.

title: natural candy
directions: Mix together; shape into balls and roll in cinnamon.
If desired, press a walnut half on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: In a large bowl (4 quart size), coat mostaccioli with oil. Drain off excess.
In a small bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic powder, mustard, pimento, parsley, onion and cucumber.
Mix with mostaccioli.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan.
Add gelatin and stir well, but do not let harden.
Cream the cream cheese with a little milk.
Whip cream (2 packages of Dream Whip or one 8-ounce Cool Whip may be used).
Add cream cheese to pineapple mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Put in mold or bowl and let harden.

title: homemade root beer
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until dissolved.
Add dry ice, stir and serve.

title: marge's party mix
directions: Melt oleo; add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over cereals and dry ingredients.
Then add the spices turning cereal while you are adding the spices.
Place in low 225° oven for 2 hours, stirring every half hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw carrot sticks, celery, onions, peppers, radishes, cauliflower and any raw vegetables.

title: ma-ma's apple pie
directions: Peel and cut up apples into chunks and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked deep dish pie shell.

title: crab cheese ball
directions: Mix crabmeat and cream cheese.
Form in a ball.
Cover with cocktail sauce. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in onion over butter.
Add 1 can water; sprinkle in 1 cup rice.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add meat, onion and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in flour, then add soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes over heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, pepper, Mazola oil and sugar and pour over beans.
Mix real good.
Chill overnight.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt.
Mix with apples.
Fill pie crust with apple mixture.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam; seal.

title: just my-size pizzas(kid's recipe)
directions: Roll out pizza dough; cut in half or the size you want.
Spoon pizza sauce over dough.
Top with ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel coffee ring(microwave)
directions: Put sugar, butter and water in round, glass dish.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Lay biscuits on top, overlapping slightly.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Roll pizza dough into 12-inch circle.
Fold loosely in half. Brush with oil and unfold.
Layer remaining ingredients on half of the circle.
Fold dough over filling. Pinch dough together. Prick top with fork.
Bake until golden brown for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt the margarine in 5-quart pan over medium heat.
Cook onions, bell pepper and garlic in margarine about 5 minutes.
Add flour; stir constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients (except shrimp, rice and parsley).
Break up tomatoes, heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chips in saucepan; add noodles.
Mix well; drop on waxed paper by the spoonful and let cool.

title: ekuri eggs(scrambled eggs with ginger)
directions: Break eggs into bowl and whisk with fork.
Add milk, salt and black pepper and stir until all ingredients are combined.
Allow egg-and-milk-mixture to foam and become frothy.
In heavy 10-inch skillet, heat oil and add ginger and fry for 10 seconds, then add onions and fry for 1 minute, until soft.
Add coriander and then turmeric.
Pour in beaten egg mixture and top with fresh chili. Reduce heat and stir with rubber spatula.
Sprinkle with cumin and serve.
Garnish with tomatoes and fresh coriander.

title: no bake pie crust
directions: Mix well and put into pie pan and spread over bottom and sides evenly.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage; run hot water into cored area to help in removing 8 outer leaves.
Set 8 leaves aside.
Chop remaining cabbage (about 6 cups) and place in baking dish; sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cut about 2 inches of the heavy vein out of reserved cabbage leaves.
Boil leaves until limp, about 3 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Beat egg with fork.

title: cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Mix milk, beaten egg, salt, Worcestershire sauce and cheese. Pour 1/2 can onion rings in cooked shell.
Pour egg and cheese mixture over onion rings.
Add crumbled bacon and remaining onion rings.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pringle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in crushed chips and nuts.
Combine thoroughly.
Form into one-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar. Place on ungreased pan; flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 14 to 16 minutes, until lightly brown on edges.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onions; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients in ovenproof dish and cook in 350° oven until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat; do not boil.
Serve.
This is a quick, easy meal and is very tasty.

title: scalloped potatoes and meat loaf
directions: Butter 8 x 12-inch pan.
Layer potatoes and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Pour green beans over potatoes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Run on high until onion is liquified.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Combine sugar, 1 stick of margarine, flour, eggs, chocolate syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and put into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Mix with corn meal.
Combine egg, oil and milk. Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, mixing just until well blended.
Do not beat.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: beef and cheese foldover
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce. Set aside.
Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent roll dough on cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides. Seal perforations.
Pat to form a 15 x 13-inch rectangle. Spread meat mixture in a 4-inch wide strip down center of dough to within 1-inch of dough edge.
Top meat with cheese slices.
Fold shorter sides of dough 1-inch over filling. Bring long sides over filling, overlapping it.
Pinch edge to seal.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing into 6 pieces.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon; stir in oats.
Combine egg, brown sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and raisins.
Add to flour mixture.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions in margarine. Combine bread crumbs, milk and onions with all other ingredients except gravy.

title: casserole for 12
directions: Mix bread crumbs and margarine; brown meat on medium heat.
Add onions.
Cook until tender, not brown.
Add next 9 ingredients. Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2 buttered casseroles.
Sprinkle top with toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Can be frozen for use later, when cooled.)

title: old-fashioned pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend in butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup.
Add pecans; pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°; bake 40 to 45 minutes longer.

title: low-cal vegetable lasagna(340 calories per serving)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch rounds.
Cut zucchini into strips.
Steam veggies 5 minutes or just until tender.
Drain.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Melt cheese in soup and milk.
Cook sausage and drain.
Cook noodles.
Toast 3 slices bread.
Mix soup mixture and cooked noodles.
Add drained sausage.
Crumble toasted bread and spread on top of dish.
Pour melted oleo over top of toasted bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Blend in 3 egg yolks and milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, for 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread small amount of custard on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with layers of wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard, making layers of each, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites on high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Spoon on top of custard.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
In large bowl, combine the beans and set aside.
In quart jar, combine the remaining ingredients. Cover and shake.
Thoroughly pour over beans.
Mix together gently.
Chill overnight or for several hours.

title: mexican bean dinner
directions: Simmer all ingredients about 30 minutes.
Put crushed Fritos on top and top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: potato and ham microwave scallop
directions: Grease ovenproof microwave dish, then put 1/3 potatoes in bottom, then 1/3 ham.
Sprinkle that with 1/3 of onion.
Mix flour, pepper and salt.
Sprinkle 1/3 over ingredients in dish.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Top with cheese.
Pour milk over all.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent that on one side.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Rotate and turn, then microwave on High 2 minutes. Remove plastic.
Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 2 (only 382 calories).

title: savory beef casserole(oven or microwave)
directions: Grease baking dish with margarine.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cover with 1 cup hot water and stir.
Empty can of Bunker Hill brown gravy and sliced beef on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake in oven 75 minutes at 350°.
If using canned vegetables, reduce time to 50 minutes.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While it is baking, melt in saucepan baste for cake.

title: mostaccioli(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Cut chili for easier melting.
Into large saucepan, add stewed tomatoes, gravy, tomato sauce and soup, thinning mixture with a couple of soup cans of water.
Simmer this mixture.
Brown beef and onions.
Add seasonings and mashed garlic (finely).
Add meat mixture to sauce.
Cook noodles in salted water with few drops of oil; drain and rinse noodles.
Add a little butter to noodles; fold noodles into sauce and meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into two layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix flour,
Crisco
and
other dry seasoning until like meal. Mix yeast
and
warm
water;
set
aside, then add with buttermilk to
flour
mixture, until stiff dough.
Let rise or as biscuits, freeze or keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic, hot pepper flakes and rosemary in olive oil on low until garlic is lightly browned.
Take the spices out of the pan and put them in blender with the can of tomatoes.
Add the blended spices and tomatoes back in with the oil.
Cook on medium for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Add sweet basil and cook as long as you like.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix well. Spoon into muffin pans. Let rise 35 to 40 minuites before baking. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chili-topped taters(serves 4)
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, brown ground beef with 1/2 cup onion and drain. Stir in chili powder, garlic powder, pepper, tomatoes and kidney beans.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
To serve, cut and break open baked potatoes.
Top with meat mixture, yogurt or sour cream, cheese and green onions.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir together just to moisten pudding mix and keep in refrigerator.

title: saucy sandwich buns
directions: Brown 209 in hot oil.
Blend in flour, seasoning, catsup, water and celery.
Cook until celery is tender, stirring constantly for about 5 minutes.
Add cheese and leave on stove until melted.
Split buns and remove some of the soft centers. Fill with mixture and toast in oven.
Serve immediately.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Press raspberries through a fine sieve.
Discard seeds.
Put juice into a small saucepan and bring to boil over moderately high heat.
Stir water and cornstarch together.
Stir into raspberry juice and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Taste and add sugar, if desired.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.
Hint: Chambord (raspberry liquor can be substituted for water).

title: fried fish
directions: Cut fish into pan size pieces.
Mix egg and milk in bowl for batter.
Dip fish in egg batter and roll in mixture of meal, salt and pepper.
Deep-fry in hot fat until browned.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix soup and water until it evens out, then add mustard, dressing, ground beef, onion and garlic powder.
Form into loaf and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store covered in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Spoon into muffin tins 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat 350° oven.
Lightly grease 10-inch deep pie plate; set aside.
Toss spaghetti with oil.
Mix beaten eggs and shredded Parmesan cheese.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mix into pie plate and form spaghetti into a crust, lining sides and bottom.
In the middle of spaghetti, put the Ricotta and Cheddar cheese mixture, then top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with dry Parmesan cheese.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: mary's fried rice
directions: Fry bacon and set aside. Save bacon grease. Scramble eggs with salt, pepper, small amount of milk (enough to make fluffy) in small amount of grease.
Dice and saute onion and bell pepper in bacon grease.
Add rice to onion, bell pepper and bacon grease. Heat and stir with grease absorbed by rice. Add water, salt and soy sauce. Cook until water is absorbed.
Add bacon and scrambled eggs to rice.
Mix in and ready to eat.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar and set aside.
Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil; pour over flour mixture while still hot.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 11 x 18 x 1-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes until springs back at 350°.
Grease bottom of pan.

title: homemade oreo cookies
directions: Stir with a fork the cake mix, oil and eggs until dry mix is gone. Roll into balls the size of nickel.
Do not flatten. Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes or until top cracks. Cool completely and ice centers.

title: basic cheese sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend until creamy.
(You can adjust consistency by adjusting milk used.)
Yields 2 cups. Approximate calories:
1 cup equals 190 calories; 1 tablespoon equals 10 calories.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: green beans in tomato basil sauce
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Meanwhile, prepare sauce.
Lightly brown the garlic in olive oil.
Remove garlic.
Let oil cool a bit and add tomato and basil; fry for 10 minutes over medium heat. Add a little water if mixture seems too dry.
Then add cooked beans with 1/4 cup more water and stir on low heat until water is evaporated and beans are just lightly frying in the tomato-oil sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You may serve at this point or even better refrigerated for a few hours.
Reheat.
Serve. Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy onion roll-ups
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Spread on one side of tortillas.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hospitality punch
directions: Combine lemon juice,
brandy, cherry juice, curacao and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over ice in punch bowl;
add champagne
and
tonic
water
just	before serving. Yield:	5 quarts.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; cover.
Blend on medium speed until smooth, approximately 30 seconds.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix bran, sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Beat eggs, milk and oil.
Add to bran mixture.
Mix thoroughly and store in refrigerator in covered container.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes. Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In a bowl stir milk into soup.
Add chicken, half the cheese, the mushrooms, pimiento and cooked macaroni; mix well.

title: quickie chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, butter and eggs.
When thoroughly mixed, add chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon 4-inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: brown 'n serve rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to form soft dough; knead.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Punch down dough and divide into 24 equal pieces.
Shape into smooth balls and place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 275°.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not let rolls brown.
Remove from pans and cook at room temperature.
Place rolls in plastic bag or aluminum foil. Store in refrigerator several days or freeze.
At serving time, brown in 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: crunchy corn dogs
directions: Combine dry pancake mix with sugar and water.
Mix well. (Batter should be quite thick.)
Dry hot dogs by patting with a paper towel.
(Batter sticks best to dry hot dogs.)
Dip hot dogs in batter, then roll in corn chips to coat well.
Fry in small amount of hot oil until golden brown and crusty.

title: salmon caesar
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in croutons, flaked salmon, green pepper, onion and chopped broccoli into a buttered 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.

title: crock-pot chicken italiano
directions: Put chicken in crock-pot (large pieces in bottom).
Mix together mushrooms, tomato sauce and water.
Add the spaghetti seasoning and blend well.
Pour the mixture over the chicken. Move chicken pieces slighlty to coat each piece.
Cook on low 8 to 9 hours.
Serve over steamed rice or noodles.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat egg yolks until thick; fold into egg whites, then fold in vanilla, flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Shape into 4 1/2-inch fingers on baking sheet covered with Pam spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar after they cool for a few minutes.

title: candied violets
directions: *Be sure to use the common wild purple violet, not the African violet (often grown as a houseplant).

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown meats together and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese into meats.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Place a heaping amount on each slice of party rye.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight jar or container.
Use 2 teaspoons of instant mix to a cup of boiling water for 1 cup of quick spicy tea.

title: date and rice krispies
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the first four ingredients until thick.
Remove from heat.
With a wooden spoon, add the nuts and Rice Krispies to the mixture.
Mix well.
Wet hands and form mixture into balls or logs.
Roll in coconut.
Place on a cookie sheet and place in refrigerator until hard.

title: broccoli tortellini summer salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets.
Cook until tender and drain.
Cook cheese tortellini
in boiling water and drain.
Combine the cheese tortellini, broccoli and onion.
Put 1/2 of the salad dressing over mixture and toss.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add additional salad dressing to taste.
tags: Italian with olive oil salad dressing

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer.
Add margarine and mix to form a grainy paste.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add egg whites, honey and vanilla to sugar mixture, and beat until smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips; blend on low speed just until combined.
Do not over mix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool, flat surface.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Add frozen strawberries. Mix until melted. Add drained pineapple and mashed bananas. Pour 1/2 mixture into 9 X 13 pan. Cool until set. Spread sour cream over top. Pour remaining jello over sour cream. Let set.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: Mix berries well with crushed pineapple.
Pour into baking dish.
Add cake mix evenly on top of berries; mash down.
Cover top with pieces of oleo.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain juice from all beans.
Put them and other ingredients into a bowl and mix lightly.
Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Cool, then pour over ingredients.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: coconut black walnut cake
directions: Beat well sugar, oil and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well and add walnuts, coconut and extract.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Pour syrup over cake while hot.
Allow to remain in pan for 4 hours to absorb syrup.

title: rose of the sea(rosa della mar)
directions: Hollow (half way) tomato, placing tuna fish into cavity of tomatoes.
Place anchovy on top of tuna.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top anchovy.
Sprinkle oregano on top of the bread crumbs.
Bake tomatoes at 350° in oven or until tomatoes are soft.
Serve with side dish of pasta.

title: smothered meatballs(good for camping)
directions: Soften bread crumbs in 1/2 cup water and mix with hamburg. Form into 24 meatballs.
Chop onion.
Heat 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Fry onion and meatballs until slightly browned.
Pour in condensed, undiluted soup and well drained peas and carrots.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over potatoes (instant, if desired).

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in butter until transparent.
Add mushrooms, flour, salt, pepper, m.s.g., garlic and paprika.
Saute beef.
Add soup (undiluted).
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and serve over rice, noodles, etc.

title: vanilla pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whisk.
Pour 1/4 cup mixture onto preheated griddle.
Turn the pancakes over when the shininess goes away.
Serve warm with syrup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: In a large bowl, stir all of the above ingredients together. Spoon into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with fat-free saltine crackers as a spread.
Yields 3 cups, 12 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: tangy fruit cup
directions: Drain canned fruit; retain juice.
To juice, blend in pudding and Tang.
Add thawed strawberries.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: salt pickles
directions: Boil ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers packed in jars and seal.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit well; mix in large bowl. Add coconut and cottage cheese along with marshmallows. Fold in sour cream and chill overnight.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare mix according to package directions.
Mix beef with evaporated milk and divide into 5 patties.
Flatten each to form a 6-inch circle.
Spoon 1/4 cup of dressing in the center of each patty.
Draw edges over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and combine soup and sauce and ketchup.
Heat until bubbly and pour over stuffed patties.
Bake uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes in moderate (350°) oven.
Can also used a can of cream of celery soup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.

title: easter bunny bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix raisins and pecans with 2 tablespoons flour mixture in small bowl.
Blend sugar and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture and carrots; mix well.
Stir in raisin mixture.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done. Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Cook
meats together in large skillet.
Brown and drain; add tomatoes (break up).
Stir in tomato paste and garlic salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan (set aside); also set aside 1 cup meat sauce and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
In ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 9-inch, alternately layer cooked noodles, meat and cottage cheese.
Spread reserved meat sauce and Mozzarella across top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease jelly roll pan, then cover with waxed paper.

Grease waxed paper top. Add water to egg yolks and beat until light yellow in color. Stir in vanilla. Add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Fold into the batter.
Beat egg whites until very stiff, then fold into the batter.
Pour batter into greased pan.

Bake in a 400° oven for 13 to 15 minutes. Invert pan at once on a cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll. Cover with a damp cloth. (The damp cloth keeps the cake moist and makes it easier to roll later.)
Let it cool completely. Unroll and spread with jelly or jam and roll again. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: squash relish
directions: Chop squash, onions and peppers.
Mix salt and water and pour over vegetables.
Let stand for 2 hours.

title: "cheese" pie
directions: Mix eggs well with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds, onion and bacon. Make dressing of remaining ingredients.
Stir dressing into first mixture and marinate at least 2 hours before serving.
Best if left overnight.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in oven to cook until it bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients into salad.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add water and 1 envelope taco seasoning. Cool and then add to salad.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
