Drop by teaspoon about 1-inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
(You may decorate with halved maraschino cherries or sprinkle with multi-colored sprinkles or sugar crystals.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once with moistened spatula.

title: banana bread (or muffins)
directions: Beat oil and sugar; add eggs and mashed bananas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes for bread; 25 to 30 minutes for muffins.
Makes 2 loaves or 24 muffins.

title: pineapple flop cake
directions: Mix by hand and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumber, onion, green pepper and salt in large bowl. Cover with water and set aside for 2 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Heat mixture.
Drain vegetables. Pour heated mixture over cucumbers.
Let set overnight in refrigerator, then freeze.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together.
Set aside.
Melt Velveeta cheese and butter in double boiler and mix well.
Then add sugar and cocoa mixture, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pat into a buttered brownie pan.
Makes 5 pounds.
This fudge freezes well and tastes great.

title: carrots almondine
directions: Peel carrots and slice thin.
Cook carrots, covered, in 1/2-inch of boiling water for 8 minutes, then drain.
Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except almonds.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon into serving dish and sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 4.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Beat 2 minutes or longer.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut outer leaves of cabbage and drop in large pan of boiling water.
Boil until leaves are workable; drain and cool.
Combine beef, onion, bell pepper, celery, rice and cabbage together.
Add 1 can tomato sauce, which has been mixed with 1 cup of water; use seasonings to taste.
Mix well.
Roll into cabbage leaves and tuck ends in.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Place rolls into a large pan or roaster.
Mix other can of tomato sauce and 1 cup water together and pour over rolls.
Cover and cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Mix onion, salt, pepper, lemon juice and mushroom soup in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Drain and flake tuna fish and add it to the soup mix, along with the rice.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and dash of paprika.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese be at room temperature.
Grate cheese. Mix all ingredients by hand.
Make into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix the Ricotta and cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Put a little meat sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and start alternating layers:
layer of noodles (raw), 1/3 meat sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat and sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Make the tomatoes into juice.
In a quart or so of juice, cook the garlic, hot peppers and onion, then run in blender.
Now put all this in the rest of the juice with the rest of the ingredients, except tomato paste.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter and chips together.
Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Bring slowly to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil briskly until it reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Line large baking dish with chips.
Brown ground beef and onion; add sauce and soups.
Spread 1/3 of the mixture over chips. Top with 1/3 cup grated cheese.
Alternate layers, cheese on top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: * fresh apple cake *
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt thoroughly.
Mix apples and sugar. Add oil, nuts, well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add mixing well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.
Good with roast beef.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp.
Chop onion very fine.
Mix shrimp, mayonnaise and onion.
Add horseradish until you like the flavor and enough ketchup to color the dip a soft pink.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken breasts moroccan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel the lemons and cut the lemon rind into julienne strips. Squeeze juice from lemon and reserve.

title: serbian cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and put in shallow 4-quart casserole.
Pour milk over.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Goes great with corned beef and boiled red potatoes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9x13 baking pan, while heating oven to 400°. Meanwhile, put peeled, whole onions in a saucepan with sweet potatoes that have been peeled and cut into 1 inch thick slices. Add water to cover, bring to boil, let stand. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, dip in egg mixture, coat with bread crumbs. Roll in butter and place in pan to form a layer. Tuck onions and sweet potatoes under chicken.
Bake 45 min to 1 hour-Basting.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Mix all together and add enough plain flour to make a stiff dough. Divide in twelve equal parts and knead each part with self-rising flour. Pat out in a ruffled edge pie pan in a thin layer. Bake until brown. When layers cool, put dried apples mixed with applesauce that has been sweetened and your favorite spice added. Makes two 6 layered cakes.

title: icebox easy lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except crust) in a bowl.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour into crust and let set in refrigerator for about 3 hours.
Serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on package.
Crumble half the cake into a large bowl, then put 1/2 can cherry pie filling, 1 box of prepared vanilla pudding, 1/2 can crushed pineapple and 1/2 bag chopped pecans.
Repeat again with other half of cake.
When finished, spread with Cool Whip and top with other half of pecans. Put in refrigerator 3 hours before you eat.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat egg; add oil, vanilla, oats, coconut, corn flakes and nuts.
Mix together flour, soda and salt. Add to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Marinate pork chops at room temperature for 1 hour in combined soy sauce, garlic and pepper. Turn chops once or twice and baste with the marinade. Broil for 30 minutes on each side, basting frequently, with chili barbecue sauce.
Serves 6.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook down until thickened.
Store in sterile pint jars.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, walnuts, soda, salt, cinnamon and milk.
Mix until well blended.
Add flour slowly, mixing until very well blended.
Bake in ungreased 11 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: lilly's turkey zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini in half and hollow each half. Cube remaining portion of zucchini and combine in a bowl with the other ingredients.
Blend until well mixed. Stuff mixture into hollowed zucchini and place in a heavily buttered baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy italian beef
directions: Remove any fat from roast.
Pour the water in crock-pot; add dry Italian dressing and stir.
Cook on low for 24 hours.
Take the roast out and shred the meat.
Add the gardinara if desired.

title: britzel
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Then line with saltine crackers.
Crackers must touch.
In pan put 1/2 pound butter and 1 cup sugar.
Cook until boils and it's foamy.
Then pour over crackers and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Then sprinkle Hershey milk chocolate chips on top immediately.
Spread around, then refrigerate until it hardens.
Peel off the foil and cut into pieces.
(Tastes like bark candy.)

title: baked apples
directions: Cut apples in half.
Cut out core.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
In small saucepan, put sugar, water and jello. Cook until sugar dissolves.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 375° until apples are tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute eggplant in batches until lightly brown, adding oil as necessary.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Layer half eggplant, zucchini, mushrooms, pepper, tomato, spinach and cheese in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Bake uncovered until vegetables are tender, 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix oleo, oil, eggs and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each one with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields approximately 5 dozen.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries through grinder or chop in blender.
Grind 1 whole orange.
Remove rind of second orange before grinding.
Core and peel apples before grinding.

title: marinated pork chops italiano
directions: In shallow dish, pour dressing over chops.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight. Remove chops; reserve dressing.
Grill or broil, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade until done.
Do not brush with marinade during last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown flour, chili powder and oil.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water gradually.
Bring to boil; turn on low.
Brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Add enchilada sauce and tomato sauce; simmer.
Dip tortilla in flour mixture; lay on plate.
Add beef and cheese.
Fold in; lay in pan.
Do all 10 tortillas; sprinkle with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Place sugar and butter over low heat until melted.
Remove and cool slightly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add other ingredients and pour into a lightly greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: candy popcorn balls
directions: Mix popcorn and gumdrops in a very large bowl.
Combine syrup and salt in saucepan; cook, stirring occasionally, to 254°. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla extract and food coloring.
Slowly pour over popcorn mixture, tossing until coated.
Quickly shape into 16 balls.

title: economical lemon icebox pie
directions: Line a pie plate with vanilla wafers, bottom and sides, then crush some wafers to make crumbs.
Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
When it thickens, add Cool Whip which has been brought to room temperature.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crust and sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender. Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave. In large pot, add Cheez Whiz and butter on low until melted with mushroom soup. Use empty can to measure milk. Add milk and broccoli. Bring to slow boil. Simmer and enjoy. Serves 10.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans a few minutes; drain.
Stir in soup, garlic juice, sugar and almonds.
Pour oleo over crumbs.
Layer beans, cheese and crumbs in casserole with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cream the cheese with the sugar.
Mix with cooled gelatin mix.
Whip the Milnot and fold into gelatin mix.
Melt butter.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs. Line pan with crumbs (press).
Pour gelatin mix into crust and chill.

title: bread on a stick
directions: Prepare green sticks, removing bark.
Make Bisquick dough as directed on package.
Make strips of dough and wind around stick. Hold 6 inches over medium coals until dough bakes and then closer to brown.
Keep turning to brown evenly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir well first 3 ingredients; add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Stir well and chill.

title: sausage tarts
directions: Pat biscuits into well-greased muffin tins.
Cook sausage and drain.
Fill muffin tins with sausage.
Mix egg with half and half and pour about 1 tablespoon over sausage.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven; sprinkle grated cheese on top and return to oven to melt cheese.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with half of chopped onion; drain.
Add ketchup, chili powder and beans.
Simmer for 20 minutes on low heat.
Top with cheese (grated), olives (halved) and the rest of the chopped onion.
Serve over favorite chips.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, green onions and cashews; mix well, stir in sour cream and Garden Caf Dressing.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate to chill and blend flavors.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving either by mixing it in, or by sprinkling on top as a garnish.

title: bean and turkey sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add sausage, onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in beans, pimiento, olives, vinegar, Tabasco sauce, oregano and parsley.
Heat through and serve.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie shell) together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach-raspberry cobbler
directions: In a bowl, combine Bisquick mix, milk, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter; set aside.
In saucepan, blend 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in peaches and raspberries.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Drop dough from tablespoon onto hot fruit, making 6 mounds.
Sprinkle additional sugar on dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until biscuits are done.
Serve with cream if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Follow pizza recipe.
Combine 1/4 cup water, 2 tablespoons oil and contents of box.
Knead dough for 5 minutes or until smooth. Divide dough in half; cover dough for 5 minutes.
Using a rolling pin, spread out dough in circle.
Place pepperoni on dough, overlapping each piece, then do same with Provolone cheese.
Roll dough up generously and pick with fork.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
Brush with butter and grated cheese and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken stew(30 gallons)
directions: The salt and pepper can be put in while the chickens are cooking and then again if it does not taste like it has enough. Usually I put salt in the chicken and potatoes while they are cooking and then add the pepper while it is cooking all together.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread butter generously over the bread, then sprinkle a teaspoon of

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers but don't pare.
Slice crosswise in thin slices. Slice onions thin.
Mix salt with cucumbers and onions and place crushed ice in mixture.
Cover and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix sugar, spices and vinegar; pour over pickles. Place over low heat and stir occasionally.
Heat the mixture to scalding, but don't boil.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat well.
Add banana mixture alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onions and bell pepper.
Mix in jar of Ragu, 1/2 jar of water, Ro-Tel and can of tomato sauce.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop and mix well the cucumbers, onions and both kinds of peppers.
Add 1 cup salt and let set 1 hour. Squeeze out relish. (Discard juice.)
Cook sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and garlic. Boil and pour over vegetables. Simmer and can. Good with pinto beans.

title: cheese strudel
directions: Lay one package of rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Lay second package of rolls on top.
Melt margarine.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce fingers
directions: Cream shortening, gradually cream in sugar, beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased 10x15 in pan and bake at 375°F for 30 minutes. Cool, then spread with frosting.

title: cottage cheese butterhorns
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Divide dough into fourths.
Roll out and fold over as butterhorns.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
While warm, ice with frosting of your choice.
You can also add slivered almonds on top, if desired.

title: green and white veggie salad
directions: Place the onion in food processor and process until finely chopped.
Add remaining ingredients except veggies and process until well blended.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add egg and orange rind.
Add flour; mix well.
Put on baking sheet by spoonful and press down.
Bake at 325° until brown around edges (approximately 10 minutes).
You can decorate with sprinkles just before they are baked thoroughly, then return to oven.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix enough powdered milk to make 8 quarts (do not add liquid). Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup water.

title: mom's blueberry tea cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in blueberries which have been rolled in a little of measured sugar and flour.
Bake in shallow greased and floured pan in moderate oven (375°) for about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 sheet cake (12 x 8 x 1-inch).

title: canned pie filling
directions: Cook until thick all ingredients, except sliced apples.
Pack sliced apples into jars.
Pour hot mixture over apples in jar. Process in water bath canner for 15 minutes.

title: quail in herbed wine sauce
directions: Rub quails with salt, pepper and garlic.
Roll in flour and brown in butter in a Dutch oven or chicken fryer.
Add the liquids slowly and then add the remaining ingredients.
Let come to a boil on top of the stove; cover and transfer to a 350° oven and cook for 1 hour.
Taste the gravy and add more salt, pepper and wine, if necessary.
Place quail on a warm platter, garnish with extra chopped parsley and serve the sauce separately.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Put peppers in boiling water a few minutes.
Mix all other ingredients together except tomato sauce.
Stuff mixture into pepper.
Place close together in deep dish.
Add sauce, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over peppers.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs separately.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately to sugar mixture with buttermilk.
Mix in raisins and Raisin Bran cereal.
Cover in refrigerator; let sit at least 8 hours before using first time.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juices from fruits.
Add water to the juices to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over the gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add the fruit, cream cheese, nuts, and Coca-Cola.
Mix well and pour into a 12 c. mold.
Chill.
Turn out onto a crisp bed of lettuce on a serving tray.

title: egg-free spice cake
directions: Boil first 9 ingredients for five minutes.
Mix 2 teaspoons soda and coffee together and add to liquid ingredients when cooled.
Mix flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda to the liquid ingredients.
Bake in a low oven at 250° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil last four ingredients.
Pour over vegetables while hot. Do not stir until cool.
Put in fridge.

title: mango marinade for fish
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a paste.
Add or subtract vinegar and shoyu to get right consistency and taste.
Place any firm fresh fish fillets in shallow pan and pour mixture over fish and let sit.
Cook fish over grill, brushing on a thick paste of marinade often.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries; stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and
bananas.
Pour
half of mixture in dish and chill until set.
When
firm, spread 1 cup sour cream over top.
Add other half
of Jell-O mixture; chill until set. Spread remaining cup of
sour
cream
over
and
sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until served.

title: orange blossom chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and pat dry breasts; place in casserole dish.
Pour juice(s) over breasts (can allow to marinate in refrigerator if desired).
Sprinkle herbs, seasonings and onions over top.
Cover with lid and bake until done; may remove lid prior to removing from oven to brown a bit.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs with mustard, salt and flour.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and gradually stir into egg mixture.
Cook until fairly thickened.

title: crab bisque
directions: Dissolve the chicken bouillon cube in the 3/4 cup boiling water.
Combine bouillon and soups in a medium sized saucepan and blend well.
Cook over moderately low heat (about 225°), just until soup reaches the boiling point, stirring frequently.
Add cream, crabmeat and sherry and heat thoroughly.
Makes about 6 cups or serves 8.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes. Pour into freezer and add milk. Let set 1 hour after freezing. Good!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir together thoroughly and then place on waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: oat bran squares
directions: Place cereal in large bowl; set aside. Melt chocolate, peanut butter and margarine over low heat; remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour melted mixture over cereal; stir until completely covered. Place cereal mixture and sugar in a container or large plastic bag and shake until cereal is completely coated in sugar. Spread on wax paper to dry. Then store in airtight container.

title: pink banana blizzard
directions: In an electric blender, combine half of all ingredients. Cover; blend until smooth and frothy, 15 to 20 seconds.
Pour into tall glasses.
Finish with the remaining ingredients.
Serve with straws or spoons.
Very tasty.

title: forget the cookies just give me that batter chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small pan, melt the margarine, add both sugars.
Stir, then allow to cool.
Mix flour, salt and soda into mixing bowl.
Add egg and vanilla to the margarine mixture.
Stir. Now, add that to the flour mix.
Blend well, then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Put bowl into refrigerator to cool for about an hour.
Roll dough into walnut sized balls.
Place on ungreased pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Serve with a side of cream cheese and crackers (like Town House brand). Keep unused in covered dish in refrigerator. Keeps very well.

title: gravy
directions: Add flour and seasoning to fat.
Add liquids and giblets; cook for at least 10 minutes.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Take large skillet and spray with cooking spray.
Spread potatoes in skillet evenly.
Crumble meat on top.
Season to taste. Add water.
Cover.
Cook on low heat until potatoes are tender. Drain.
Crack eggs on top of meat, as many as needed to serve. Re-cover.
Shred cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
When egg tops are white, re-cover and cook until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and serve.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan.
Beat all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.
Caution:
Do not overcook.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add flour alternately with grated zucchini.
Add vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in 2 greased 5 x 9 x 3-inch loaf pans for 1 hour at 325° until cake test comes out clean.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: You will need 8 pint jars with lids.

title: apricot-lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in cold water and ginger ale.
Pour into 9-inch ring mold.
Chill until partially set. Fill centers of apricot halves with cream cheese balls, rolled in nuts.

title: pumpkin tea loaf
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Put in 2 (9 x 5-inch) or 3 disposable greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Freezes very well.
Can add any kind of nuts and chopped dates.

title: spiced german pot roast
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat over medium heat. Season meat with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat; add water. Simmer for about 3 hours, until tender.
Place meat on warm platter.
Keep warm while making Spicy Gravy.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan, combine cornmeal, salt and water.
Stir and bring to a boil over high heat.
Remove from heat and beat in milk and eggs.
Pour into pan. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix
liquid
from asparagus with one can mushroom soup. In Pyrex
dish, 1 layer of saltine crackers, 1 layer of grated cheese, 1
layer
of
boiled eggs and 1 layer of asparagus.
I usually make
two
layers.
Pour liquid and mushroom soup over ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions. Bake in sheet cake pan (9 x 13 x 2). While cake is baking, mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes. When cake is done, pour hot pineapple and sugar over hot cake. Let cool completely. When cake is cooked, prepare instant pudding as directed on box. Pour over cake. Spread with Cool Whip. Top with coconut and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: coconut butterballs
directions: Cream butter with 2 tablespoons sugar until blended.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Shape in 3 dozen balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet. Chill 15 minutes, then bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes, or until very lightly browned.
Roll at once in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together, then pour the following dressing mixture over salad:

title: no bake cherry o'cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add Eagle Brand milk slowly, beating thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and continue beating until mixture is smooth and thick.
Spoon filling into pie crust. Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs. Mix well. Pour in syrup and flavoring. Stir in oatmeal and pecans. Pour in pie shell; bake for 1 hour at 350°. (Fifty minutes may be enough!)

title: beef stew
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine flour and pepper; dredge meat in flour mixture, reserving the excess.
Cook meat, 3/4 cup onion and reserved flour mixture in oil in a Dutch oven over low heat until meat is lightly browned.
Add water and next 5 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Place teaspoon size amount on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place kisses in oven and turn off oven immediately.
Leave in oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until dry.
Makes 60 kisses.

title: patis
directions: Boil the potatoes until done.
Mash the boiled potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cilantro.
Mix well.
Take a small amount of the mixture and flatten in the palm of your hand.
Place 1/6 of the cooked ground beef in the center and cover with more of the potato mixture.
Dip this in the beaten egg and then coat it with bread crumbs.
Repeat process with the other three eggs.
Deep fry in hot oil until browned.
Drain.
Serve with ketchup.
Serves 6.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Blend soup and milk.
Stir into macaroni and cheese with tuna, mushrooms and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Mix well and fold in the peas.
Put in casserole dish that has been buttered or sprayed with nonstick agent.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Spray cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Combine salmon, bread crumbs, celery, onion, egg substitutes, parsley, lemon juice, celery seed, pepper and garlic powder in bowl; mix well with fork.
Shape salmon mixture into 6 oval patties.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Turn over with spatula and bake 5 more minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter over moderate heat and stir in sugar and pineapple, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Whisk eggs, milk and salt.

title: sweet sour cucumbers
directions: About 1 hour before serving or up 2 days ahead, in large bowl, combine ingredients..
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 cups.

title: stove top meat loaf(35 minutes)
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup with beef, crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves.
In a skillet, brown on both sides in the shortening.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Top with remaining soup, water and horseradish.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings. Mushroom or tomato rice may also be used.

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Wash peaches, peel and slice.
Put peaches in a baking dish.
Sift flour with sugar, salt and cinnamon into a medium bowl.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Sprinkle evenly over peaches. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden brown. Serve warm with light cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and mix.
Add egg; beat well.
Mix well the next 4 ingredients and add, alternating with applesauce, to creamed mixture.
Spoon into 12 well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coco lopez coconut cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients 2 to 3 minutes; add Coco Lopez and mix about 1 minute. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese salad for ritz crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on Ritz crackers.

title: turtle fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil to 234°.
Remove from heat and add chips.
Stir well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
You may not want to completely melt caramels for a lumpy fudge.

title: ma-ma eva's light fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275 degrees.

Cream butter and sugar together, add egg yolks and beat until well blended, and add most of flour, and save a small portion of it to dredge your fruits and nuts in. Add flavors and wine and blend well.
Dredge fruits and nuts in remaining flour in a large pan.
Place batter into pan with dredged fruits and nuts and blend together with a large spoon.
Beat egg whites with mixer until they become foamy looking and mix them into batter, fruits, and nuts.
Line cake pan with wax paper and bake for 1 1/2 hours for loaf pans or 2 1/2 hours for tube pan.
When cake is done, you may pour wine on top of cake, before wrapping tightly and periodically while it sits before cutting.

title: linguine with shrimp sauce
directions: Cook linguine 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Brown shrimp, garlic and parsley in oil over gentle fire for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato puree.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add oregano and basil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour shrimp sauce over linguine.
Serves 4.

title: the mayor's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Cream shortening until fluffy. Slowly add sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Let foam. Alternately add flour and milk.
Add the melted chocolate.
Mix. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, that has been greased, then lined with waxed paper and greased again.
Bake at 325° about 35 minutes.
Turn out on waxed paper on a board and remove paper. Cool.
Flip cake over.

title: microwave butter toffee
directions: In a large, microwave-safe bowl, mix butter, water and corn syrup.
Microwave on High power 4 minutes; stir.
Stirring every 2 minutes, microwave 6 to 8 minutes longer or until mixture thickens and turns golden.
Stir in vanilla.

title: fruit chiffon pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together well. Add fruit juice and stir. Bring to boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Set to cook. Chill milk; whip until peaks.
Stir into hot mixture.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, carrots, onions, olives and pimentos; add dressing and sugar. Toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours, stirring frequently. Just before serving, stir in walnuts.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add alternately with pineapple juice.
Dredge fruit with flour.
Add to cake mixture and mix well.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or until done.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
Refrigerate.
May be wrapped in wine soaked cheesecloth when cooled.

title: mother gerhardt's citation brownies
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add this alternately with milk to creamed eggs and sugar.
Pour in melted butter.
Grease or spray with Pam an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put wax paper on bottom of pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until it tests done when it rolls away from edges of pan. Remove from oven and let sit for 3 to 5 minutes on cooling rack. Then turn out and remove wax paper.
Makes 18 (1 1/2 x 1 1/2 x 3/4-inch) brownies.

title: beer boat
directions: Put beer in blender first.
Blend in other ingredients.
Remove insides of bread loaf and replace with cheese mixture.
Dunk removed pieces of bread into cheese mixture.

title: lime jello mold with pears
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1/2 cup.
Dice pears and set aside. Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water; add cold water, pear syrup and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan (I use metal mold sprayed with Pam).
Chill until set, but not firm.
Gelatin should be sticky to the touch.

title: wassail(hot drink)
directions: Put in large pan.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
(Can also be put in crock-pot.)

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large bowl put beans and cover with water.
Microwave on High for 30 minutes.
Make sure they are covered with water at all times.
(Or you could soak the beans overnight.)
Cook on medium-high with onion, bell pepper, garlic, salt and pepper, stirring often).
When beans start to become soft (or sticking to the side of the pot), add meat.
(If using sausage, brown first.) When beans become real soft and creamy, they are done.
If you want them creamier, add the stick of margarine when they have been turned off.
Serve over rice.
They are good with corn bread. This recipe is very filling and goes a long way.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Boil 1 cup of berries, water and sugar in saucepan until thoroughly cooked.
Push through a sieve.
Add cornstarch to strained mixture and boil 1 minute.
Chill.
Add 3 cups of fresh berries and chill again in precooked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Also good made with strawberries or raspberries.

title: buttercream icing
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening with mixer; add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well at medium speed.
Scrape sides of bowl often.
When all sugar is added, icing will appear dry.
Add milk; beat at high speed until light and fluffy.

title: root beer slushie
directions: Pour condensed milk and root beer into ice cream freezer, mixing together.
Freezer until mixture is thick and slushy. Tastes like a root beer float.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop on parchment paper or greased, foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: peach praline pie(read all instructions before starting crust for 2 crust pie)
directions: Place foil in pie plate and cover generously with oleo.
Press pecans into oleo and cover with 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Place 1 crust on top of nuts.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix remaining ingredients and adjust sugar to ripeness of fruit.
Spoon into crust.
Cover with top crust; seal, flute and prick with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce to 375° for 40 minutes.
Be sure to cool completely before turning upside down carefully.
Remove foil.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs.
Stir; add yogurt; stir again.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Do not overmix.
Add vanilla; stir in blueberries.
Fill paper lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until tops are brown.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Heat milk, soup and cheese together. Add instant rice and pour over broccoli.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warn water.
Add sugar, salt and about half of the flour.
Beat well for 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening, and gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator, punching it down occasionally, as dough rises.

title: cheese dip for crackers
directions: Soften cream cheese and Velveeta slices in microwave until able to mix thoroughly and smooth.
Add in garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Mix well.
Garnish with paprika and sliced green olives.

title: mrs. dulls 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream
the
butter and sugar well using electric mixer. Add egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients, then add them alternately with the
milk.
Add
vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in a 325° oven until done.
Cake can be baked in tube pan, loaf
pan
or
rectangular pan.
Frost, if desired. For pound cake, add 1 extra stick of butter.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Brown onion in hot oil. Drain. Pour all ingredients in a big pot except for seasoning. Mix well. Cover top of sauce with seasoning. Mix well. Again cover sauce with seasoning. Cook on low heat all day. Stir occasionally. BUT DO NOT scrape bottom of pot when stirring.

title: sausage lima casserole
directions: Place limas in casserole and salt lightly.
Mix in sausage. Cut into small chunks.
Top with onion slices.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until beans are tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and serve with crackers!!!

title: green pasta
directions: Boil pasta until done.	Drain, do not rinse.
Stir in 2 or 3 dollops of pesto.
Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top individually.

title: roast turkey with giblet gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
The turkey can be baked with or without stuffing.
Rub the inside of the cavity with salt and pepper, then rub these same seasonings on the outside skin.
If turkey is to be cooked without stuffing, place a large onion, carrot and a stalk of celery inside the turkey cavity.
If you prefer stuffing inside, use cornbread dressing or the type you like best.
(A good cornbread dressing is provided by Doris Owens and is included in this cookbook.)

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Combine the soda crackers, graham crackers and melted butter or margarine.
Put in a cake drip pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.
Combine the 2 packages of butterscotch pudding; mix it with the milk.
Mix in the butterscotch ice cream.
Put this mixture in the crust.
Top with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with the shredded chocolate.
Will keep in the freezer for 1 month.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in pan. Spread German chocolate cake mix (made according to package directions).
Combine until smooth the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonful on top of cake.
Do not mix or stir.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Bon appetit!

title: mexican chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburger and break up.
In large pot, add steak and kidney beans, tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cut onion into small pieces and crush garlic.
Fry in a little butter until slightly brown.
Add to pot.
Cut green pepper into fine pieces and add.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
In a mixing bowl, beat 3 eggs until frothy.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well and pour into pan.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Cover with pecans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: steak or chicken shish kabobs
directions: Slice meat into 4 x 1/4-inch strips and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a shallow dish.
Add steak, coating well. Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Remove steak from refrigerator and place on skewers.
Add fresh vegetables if you like.
Grill 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until desired level of doneness is reached.
Baste frequently with marinade.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and sour cream.
Add all ingredients except 1 cup of bread cubes.
Place in casserole and top with remaining bread cubes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and brown for 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil in medium mixing bowl.
Mix well. Stir in carrots and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: wedding or birthday cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If icing is too thin, add more Crisco.

title: skinny pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Continue adding water until mixture resembles heavy cream.
With a soup ladle, drop mix into hot oil (1/4-inch) to form small pancakes.
Cook until edges are brown; flip.
Repeat.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cover bottom of large shallow casserole with dried beef. Place chicken breasts on the beef; place a piece of semi-fried, limp, bacon on each piece of chicken.
Mix casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours and 45 minutes. White wine may be added.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a
large bowl, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar,
zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
In another bowl, sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture, stirring to mix completely.
Fold
in
nuts.
Pour
into 3 greased and floured loaf
pans.
Bake
at
until done, about 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in saucepan until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Place flour in large bowl; add milk mixture and stir until blended.
Cover and rise in warm place about 1 hour and 20 minutes (double).
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Dip each square in melted butter.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine and chocolate in milk until melted.
Pour over bread. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolks.
Blend sugar into yolks.
Mix egg yolk mixture into bread mixture. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Serve warm. Top with whipped nondairy topping.

title: carrots thetis
directions: Put the carrots, onion, celery and bell pepper through a food processor fitted with the thin slicing disk or slice them thinly by hand.
In a large skillet or pot with a lid, melt the butter. Add the vegetables and seasonings and saute gently for 15 minutes. Add the mushrooms, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Stir the mixture until it is thoroughly heated and the vegetables are limp, but not soggy.
Serves 12.

title: pasta with vodka tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion, garlic and Italian seasonings and saute until onion is translucent, about 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, reserved juices and Prosciutto and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vodka and simmer 5 minutes.
Add cream and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Simmer until sauce thickens slightly, about 4 minutes. Add pasta and stir until sauce coats pasta.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve, passing remaining 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese separately.

title: sausage-vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart casserole, stir together the water, milk and packet from potato mix. Add potato slices, sausage, mixed vegetables and onion.
Mix.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients; bake in casserole dish for 1 hour.

title: fresh veggie appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 rectangles.
Press onto bottom and up sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing, sour cream, dill and onion salt until well blended.
Spread on crust.
Top with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate; cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: empanadas ricas de calabaza
directions: Pour beer into bowl.
Add lard.
Let stand at room temperature for about 3 hours.
Work flour into beer mixture.
After 3 hours, use enough flour until dough forms.
Form 3-inch balls and roll out into 5 to 6-inch diameter circles.
Fill with pumpkin or favorite fruit or meat filling.
Bake at 425° until golden brown and dust in sugar and cinnamon mixture (1 cup sugar to 1 teaspoon cinnamon). Can be frozen for 1 month.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours. Bake, covered, first hour, then put chow mein noodles on top and bake, uncovered, for at least 1/2 hour.

title: heavenly fluff salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Can be varied by using different flavors of jello and different fruit.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of water until tender; drain. Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic until tender in butter.
Mix with eggplant and eggs.
Put in casserole in layers: Eggplant mixture, cheese, bread crumbs and top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta and vegetables with dressing in a large bowl.
Add as much Parmesan as you like and toss together.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas, mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients, milk, and vanilla.
Add nuts and mix. Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail icing
directions: Put sugar, egg whites, cream of tartar and water in top of double boiler.
Stir well and place over boiling water, being careful that water in lower part does not touch upper pan.
Beat constantly with rotary beater until mixture holds a point, 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from over the water and add vanilla.

title: blueberry banana muffins
directions: Beat together bananas and egg until creamy.
Add milk and oil. Beat in flour mixture.
Gently add blueberries.
Spoon batter into oiled and floured muffin tins or use papers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Add chopped pecans, pour into baked pie crusts.
Garnish with whole pecans.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, approximately 45 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Melt butter and add onion.
(I melt my butter in the microwave, this cooks the onion, too.)
Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix Veg-All to the butter, onions and cheese.

title: mexi turkey d'light
directions: Cook turkey about 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add taco seasonings and water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place kidney beans in an 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer cooked turkey on top of beans, then tomatoes.
In a small bowl, mix corn bread mix, adding water according to package directions, with onion, cheese and peppers. Spread mixture on top of turkey and beans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until corn bread mix is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta and broccoli in garlic(easy and delicious)
directions: In a frypan, saute garlic and oil.
Add chicken broth.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook until desired taste of broccoli.
Cook short time for hard broccoli or longer for softer broccoli.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in heavy saucepan until nearly crisp.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally; drain.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add clam liquid, tomatoes, water, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper to saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add potatoes.
Cook for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and corn.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in margarine; discard bay leaf.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: ben's chili(spicy)
directions: Use 4-quart saucepan.
Add oil and brown meat.
Add and saute peppers, onions, garlic and celery until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer 2 to 4 hours.
Mash potato and return to pot.
Make adjustments desired.
Amount not used may be frozen.

title: chunky chicken rice soup(kids in the kitchen)
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until lightly browned. Remove chicken. Add water, broth, vegetables and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes. Add to soup.
Cover and cook on low heat for approximately 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Stir in rice and parsley.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast; mix well.
Blend in egg.
Add flour and mix until dough is well blended. Put into greased bowl and cover. Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Shape dough on well floured board.
Let rise in warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: better than sex cake(3rd place - hall of fame)
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter and mix thoroughly.
Press on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and one carton Cool Whip; beat and spread over first layer.
Combine milk and chocolate pudding and beat 3 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread second container Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Drain juice from cherries.
Add enough milk to measure 1 cup liquid.
Chop cherries and walnuts; sift 1/4 cup flour over. Cream 1/2 pound butter.
Add 2 cups sugar, beating until smooth. Add 4 egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add fruits and nuts.
Sift 3 cups sifted all-purpose flour with the baking powder and baking soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and cherry juice.
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 10-inch greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan or pan of similar shape.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Sauce: Brown chopped meat in oil. Add onion, garlic, tomato paste (diluted with water), parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaves. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until stiff.
Add the sugar; beat.
Fold in the cake flour, sugar and baking powder. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water, peanut butter and cooking oil to a boil in large pan.
Take off heat and add mixture of flour, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and soda.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and mix with sugar and flour.
Add syrup and eggs.
Beat until frothy.
Add salt, vanilla and pecan halves. Pour into 9 inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 325.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough in 1/8-inch slices and line pizza pan, overlapping.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on pie.

title: crab newburg(or tuna, salmon, lobster)
directions: Use low heat.
Melt butter in pan. Stir in flour. Add remaining ingredients and heat. Serve over rice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown (if you drain off fats, you may need to add a little liquid).
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes. Add soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together well and fry in deep fat.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together brown sugar, white sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, milk and eggs.
Sift together and then stir into the batter the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
By hand, fold in oats, chocolate chips and walnuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat bacon grease in iron skillet. Add uncooked rice and stir until evenly browned. Add chopped onion and green bell pepper. Stir. Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Stir. Add chicken broth and mix well. Cover, turn heat to low and cook until liquid is gone.
Rice will be tender to flaky. Set on warm burner until you prepare the rest of your meal.
Can add cooked chicken pieces or ground beef.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Bake 1/2 of mix in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
In top of double boiler, melt
butter, caramels and Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and pour over cake in pan.
Pour remaining cake mix on top of caramel mixture.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: avocado salad
directions: Cut avocados in half and remove the seeds; slice and toss with lemon juice. Pour dressing over.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large oiled casserole dish (except for green beans).
Top with green beans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma lay's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add salt, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Add these alternately with the buttermilk.
Combine soda and boiling water. Add to batter.
This will seem thin.
Yields 3 (8-inch) layers or one 9 x 12-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and Karo syrup until clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved (red food coloring may be added, if desired).
Cool.
Add strawberries. Pour into baked pie crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix with mayonnaise, cheese and onion; pour in casserole dish.
Melt oleo and mix with cracker crumbs.
Put on top of vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: corned beef soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, onions,
bouillon
and
spice in water until potatoes are fork-tender.
Add corned beef, tomatoes and cabbage until cabbage is done.

title: uncle larry's favorite chicken!
directions: Mix together all ingredients and marinate chicken overnight or at least 4 hours.
Grill for about 20 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Combine the egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture, then roll in Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs.
Put on greased pan.
Put 1/2 teaspoon butter on top of each slice.
Broil until golden brown.
Turn over, add butter, bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water and chill.
Do not let it get hard, just firm.
Melt butter and combine with the crushed graham crackers.

title: poppie york's "famous" baked beans casserole
directions: 1. Place bacon in cold fry pan.
Set dial at 320°.
Fry until beginning to get crisp.

title: quick cheese puffs
directions: Separate biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Roll each piece in melted butter and then in grated cheese (Parmesan and Cheddar).
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Add seasonings to taste. Stir in eggs: pour into lightly greased 2 quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Yield 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm set.

title: white sangria
directions: Place fruit and cinnamon sticks in a bowl and add brandy. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Add sugar, fruit and brandy mixture to wine.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, remove cinnamon sticks; add club soda and vodka.
Pour over crushed ice.
Add maraschino cherries for more color.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash- drain juice, add to all ingredients.
Mix well. Place in 8 x 8 casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pepperoni eggplant crisps
directions: Wash eggplant.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Do not peel.
On half of the slices, place Mozzarella or Jack cheese.
Top with 2 or 3 pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Top with remaining eggplant halves.

title: rolled rib roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper to taste.
Place fat side up on rack in shallow pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Let roast stand for 20 minutes before serving.
Serve with browned whole potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges.
Add sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk, mixing until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple to boil.
Stir in jello and pour in Coca-Cola.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add other ingredients.

title: spanish steak
directions: Place beef roast in pan and add juice over it.
Slice onions and green pepper onto beef and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Add cabbage and vinegar together, then let stand for 30 minutes.
Heat for 1 minute, then cool.
Drain this mixture and add all other ingredients.
You can also freeze if you wish.

title: punch
directions: Mix and pour over crushed ice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Spread sausage in mixing bowl; sprinkle with the cheese.
Mix together.
Gradually add 2 1/4 cups biscuit mix.
If mixture is a little soft, add remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix.
When mixture is ready, shape into balls the size of marbles.
Cook at 375° until brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: raisin pie
directions: Place a heaping cup of raisins in enough water to cover; simmer gently for about 3 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add margarine and egg.
Spread the raisins in the pie crust.
Gently spread mixture over raisins.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat and onion; add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve open-faced over buns.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add 1/2 package dressing mix and 1/2 package of seasoning mix.
Put in baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and put over dressing.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: orange, date and pecan bread
directions: Wash and squeeze orange and add to the juice enough boiling water to make one cup.
Remove pulp from orange and put peeling through grinder.
Combine with dates, orange liquid, sugar, butter and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serve with soft cream cheese mixed with honey, lemon juice, orange juice, dash of salt and a few drops of almond extract.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, ham and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soups together with milk and pour over top. Cover and cook in slow cooker 8 to 10 hours.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple together and boil a few minutes, stirring.
Add cream cheese and mix.
Let stand until it begins to jell.
Add apricots, pecans and celery.
Last fold in Dream Whip. Pour into flat casserole and chill.

title: instant hot chocolate mixgroves, texas
directions: Mix well and store in air tight container.

title: chunky chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Blend chicken broth and soup and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken. Saute onion; add to chicken.
Mix melted butter, flour and buttermilk until it forms soft dough; add parsley flakes.
Spoon dough over top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine and cook on medium for 20 minutes until tender. Gradually add 3 cups milk to 4 tablespoons flour.
Add mixture to vegetables and cook until thick.
Add 1
pound Velveeta cheese, cut in cubes.
Stir until melted.

title: johnson's cream dream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare pie crust for an 8 or 9-inch two crust pie.
In medium bowl, stir cornstarch into cream.
Add other ingredients, being careful not to "break down" beaten egg white.
Pour into crust-lined pie plate.
Cut hole, approximately 1 inch in diameter, in remaining crust and carefully lay over top. Seal (flute) around edges.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour. Check 3/4 way through cooking time and if bubbling too vigorously, turn temperature down to 300°.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking soda.
Cream together peanut butter and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; beat well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Take out and place Hershey Kisses in middle, pressing down.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes more.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into muffin pans coated with cooking spray, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
16 muffins (about 95 calories each).

title: angel pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in double boiler until thickened; let stand until very cold.
Fold egg whites into cooled pineapple mixture.
Do not beat.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In mixing bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half of the flour.
Beat well.
Add egg and shortening.
Add remaining flour.
Knead until dough is satiny.
Let rise about 1 hour or until double.
Make into rolls and place on baking sheet. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice cashew casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add rice and stir. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir to mix well.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: kielbasa appetizers
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well. Then add final 3 ingredients and mix together.

title: vegetable-spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Dip is great served in a scooped out loaf of King Hawaiian bread.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut the tenderloin into 1 1/2 inch x 1/4-inch strips; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice in a small bowl.
Set pineapple aside.
To juice, add ketchup, water, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and ginger.
Stir until smooth.
Heat oil in a large skillet on high; stir-fry pork and onion for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir pineapple juice mixture; add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve immediately over rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fritter batter
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Melt and cool remaining 2 tablespoons of shortening and set aside.
Add just enough water to flour mixture so dough holds together and can be handled easily.
Knead on a lightly floured board until smooth (30 seconds), adding only enough flour to work dough.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Cut together with pastry blender or use two knives.
Add egg and milk.
Mix until blended well.
If you overmix, it will not be as tender. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Make the crust by combining the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar in a medium bowl. Stir well enough to coat all of the crumbs with the butter, but not so much as to turn the mixture into paste. Keep it crumbly. Press the crumbs onto the bottom and about 2/3 of the way up the sides of the spring-form pan. You don't want the crust to form all of the way up the back of each slice of cheesecake. Bake the crust for 5 minutes, then set it aside until you are ready to fill it.

title: guacamole appetizer
directions: Combine avocado, lemon juice, onion, salt and chili powder. Spread top with mayonnaise or salad dressing, sealing to edges of bowl; chill.
When ready to serve, stir in the mayonnaise or salad dressing.
If desired, add bacon, crumbled.
Serve with corn chips.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Cook hamburger, onions and tomato sauce. Add chopped stewed tomatoes and catsup. Add all spices one at a time; simmer for about 20 minutes. Add macaroni; stir well. If too stiff, add tomatoes or tomato juice.

title: old-time tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, salt, vanilla extract and lemon extract in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with mixture of buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Store in plastic bags in airtight containers.
Yield: 100 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Let stand.
Melt margarine in 10 x 10-inch pan or dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Stir to a smooth paste.
Pour into pan over butter.
Do not stir.
Add strawberries, 1/4 cup strawberry juice and juice of 1 lemon.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour or until pie is golden brown at 325°.

title: susan's chicken soup
directions: Clean and place quartered chicken in large pot of water.
Let boil and skim residue off top.
Place cut up carrots, celery and celery greens and onion into pot.
Let it cook approximately 1 hour.
Remove chicken and vegetables from pot.
Place all vegetables in a blender with some liquid from soup.
Put on medium speed until all vegetables are pureed.
Add mixture to soup and season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic and a drop of sugar for sweetness.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda, in a glass dish. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir. Microwave 1 minute; add soda and stir.
Pour over popped corn in a brown paper bag.
Roll down bag and microwave in bag for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake hard and microwave for 45 seconds.
Shake hard again to mix and pour out on foil or cookie sheet to cool.
(Do not double recipe.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together chicken, soup and broth and pour into greased pan or dish.
Add one layer of mixture and 1 layer of sliced eggs, alternately.
Mix together milk, oleo and flour.
Pour this mixture over pie and bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and chopped onion; pour over potatoes.
Mix in grated cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta chicken and sundried tomatoes
directions: Heat broth to a boil.
Pour over sundried tomatoes and leave about 30 minutes, until tomatoes are soft.
Meanwhile, in a nonstick frypan, heat oil over low heat.
Add onions.
Cook, covered, until very soft (20 minutes).
Uncover and raise heat to medium, stirring often, for 10 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and pack cucumbers in jars with a head of dill and 1 or 2 cloves of garlic at bottom and same on top, plus a dash of alum. Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and water together, bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Rinse apples and cut each apple into about 6 pieces.
Do not peel.
Remove the core and seeds.
Place apple slices in 1 or 2 large pans with 1/8 inch of water in the bottom of each pan. Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until apples are soft.
Pour off extra liquid.
Press apples through colander.
Add sugar.
Put mixture into 1 or 2 saucepans.
Reheat so sugar will dissolve and add a scant tablespoon of lemon juice per saucepan.
Then sweeten with sugar and season with nutmeg and cinnamon to taste.
If you like pink applesauce, add some red food coloring.
Put applesauce in quart jars, leaving 1-inch air space at the top of the jar.
Let cool several hours and freeze. This keeps well for 4 to 6 months.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the cucumbers with salt.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Drain liquid.
Add onions, vinegar and pepper.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serves:
6. Per serving:
35 calories, 1 gm total fat, 2 mg chol, 197 mg sodium, 6 gm chol, 2 g pro.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Beat egg
yolks
until	light.	Add
sugar and blend in well. Add
apples, lemon	juice
and
grated rind.
(When you grate the apples, put them in the lemon juice so they will not turn dark.) Cook until thick.
Add butter and salt.

title: sausage in sauce
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces.
Boil in water 20 minutes.
Pour out water.
Put sausage in glass baking pan.
Add everything except brown sugar and wine.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Add wine and brown sugar and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar candy
directions: Cook sugar, salt, syrup, butter and milk to soft boil stage (238° on candy thermometer). Cool without stirring to 110° on candy thermometer. Add vanilla and beat until it holds its shape. Add nuts. Mix and then pour onto a buttered platter. When completely cooled, cut into squares.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Allow butter or margarine to soften at room temperature. Place flour in a medium to large bowl.
Add softened butter or margarine.
Then, mix in milk gradually until dough is smooth.
If it's a little sticky, add a little flour for smoothness.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Combine uncooked rice with soup, add water and mix.
Put mixture in a casserole dish.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Place on top of rice mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mint pineapple refresher
directions: Combine jelly and water in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring frequently until jelly melts.
Let cool.
Stir in juices; cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Yields 7 cups.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Spray 3-quart casserole with Pam.
Layer vegetables, except tomatoes, and meat, seasoning each layer.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350° or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cut cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out fluid.
Mix cabbage, celery and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute and cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and freeze.
Yield depends on size of cabbage. Slaw is crisp and fresh when defrosted.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up salad ingredients first and mix well.
Add beans, Fritos, shredded cheese and salad dressing last.
Mix well. Serve immediately or Fritos become soggy.
Great for a party or an outdoor barbecue.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: *Use beans such as cannellini or pinto.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Chill before serving.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Parboil, do not overcook. Peel when cooled. Grate into a greased Pyrex baking dish.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Dot with butter and pour half and half up the sides of the dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Cream in all ingredients until smooth. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
Top with grated cheese and butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make the day before!

title: caramel oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Next add butter until mix is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with nuts and chocolate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a medium-size bowl, shred lettuce.
Mix together onion, celery and pepper.
Place these vegetables on top of lettuce.
Add English peas as next layer.
Beat enough mayonnaise with sugar to make a layer 1/4-inch deep over the peas.
Add grated cheese layer and sprinkle with bacon on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Cream oleo; add coconut, sugar, vanilla, vinegar, salt and beaten eggs.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in low heated oven at 300°.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, English cheese, Tabasco, onion, garlic and nuts.
Roll into logs or balls; sprinkle with paprika and refrigerate.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put green tomatoes in grinder.
Sprinkle with salt and leave overnight.
Drain and press, then add sugar.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Stir to prevent burning.
Add mace, cinnamon, cloves and up to 1 quart of vinegar.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: pineapple slushies
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil, then cool.
Mix altogether in very large pot.
Spoon into containers and freeze.
When serving, spoon into glasses about 3/4 full and add 7-Up or ginger ale. Makes about 8 or 9 quarts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat whole egg	and
3	egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Mix
cornstarch,	sugar
and butter together; add to beaten eggs.
Pour	scalded
milk over eggs and sugar mixture; mix well.
Cook in
the
top
of
a double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into
baked pie shell.
Top with whip cream and coconut.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo syrup together in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan until it spins a thread from spoon. Add raw peanuts stirring constantly until mixture turns brown. Remove from heat. Add soda and stir well. Spread on buttered cookie sheet and let cool. Break out of pan and store.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Heat in double boiler.
Serve warm in fondue dish.
Add reserved liquid if dip appears too thick, a little at a time. Serve with vegetables.

title: el dorado beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain, then add onion, garlic and tomato sauce while still in skillet. In a bowl, combine sour cream and cottage cheese with chilies. Crush chips to cover bottom of well greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Add 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 sour cream and cheese mixture, 1/2 olives and 1/2 cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables for 5 minutes, drain.
Mix vegetables with next 6 ingredients and put in large baking dish.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Melt stick of margarine and drizzle over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate banana pudding
directions: Mix instant
pudding as directed on the package.
Slice bananas into
1/4-inch slices.
Crumble vanilla wafers, but do not crush them
too
much.
Mix all together and top with Cool Whip.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Scour a 1 pint jar.
Boil Brussels sprouts 5 to 10 minutes, depending on size.
Mix the water, vinegar and salad oil. Add the Italian dressing. Shake all well and pour over sprouts.
Seal and store in refrigerator.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add warm mashed potatoes and egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix vanilla and milk.
Add all ingredients alternately to butter mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour two cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven until straw comes out clean in center of cake, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.
Over medium heat, melt sugar (do not stir, just shake the skillet).
When browned, add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil.
Mix other ingredients (except egg whites and vanilla).
Add melted sugar and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla and put in a baked pie shell. Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Put on pie filling and bake until brown.

title: mexican pizza
