directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, spread the bean mixture over the bottom of the dish.
Peel the avocados and put in blender with lemon juice and garlic.
Blend until smooth.
Spread over bean dip.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread in a layer over the avocado mixture.
Top this with diced onions, chopped tomatoes, chopped jalapeno peppers (or you may sprinkle with hot salsa or picante sauce and shredded cheese). Serve with tortilla chips to dip with.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: In a large bowl combine lemonade concentrate and 1 can of water.
Add apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Serve over ice with pineapple wedges.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain, then stir in spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce, water and mushrooms.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, 1/3 meat, 1/2 cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with noodles, meat, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Last layer noodles.
Spread with meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes after hot and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces in bottom of salad bowl. Next cut bite size pieces of cauliflower.
Spread mayonnaise over lettuce and cauliflower evenly; cover completely.
Sprinkle dressing; mix over mayonnaise.
Fry bacon crisp, crumble over dressing mix.

title: india relish beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Cook chopped onion in grease from bacon.
Drain off grease.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in a Pyrex casserole.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix together hash browns, 1/2 cup oleo, pepper, onion and soup.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Pour on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: beth's pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt for 10 minutes. Wash and cap okra. Pack okra into jars. Place the listed dill, garlic and peppers into each jar. Pour the hot mixture over okra to cover. Seal; process. Allow 3 weeks to pickle. Yields about 10 pints. Chill before serving. Quick and easy!

title: fried bread
directions: In a small saucepan, heat buttermilk until bubbles form at edge of pan.
Set aside to cool slightly.
When buttermilk has cooled, stir in egg, oil, sugar and yeast until well combined; set aside 5 minutes for yeast to soften.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk and rice until rice is done, the more you stir it the creamier it will be.
Take it off the stove and add the sugar, egg and vanilla.
Cook about 5 more minutes and pour into dish to cool.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cook over medium heat until thickens, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat (set aside).
Beat egg whites at medium speed until stiff.
Beat yolks slightly; while with mixer running, add slowly to egg whites.
Now, gradually stir in about 1/3 of corn meal mixture. Then add this egg white mixture to the remaining hot corn meal mixture.
Stirring constantly, pour entire corn meal/egg white mixture into a 1 1/2-quart deep casserole dish, coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes a delicious corn bread substitute except you serve it with a spoon.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liner; fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cherry when first take out of oven.
Makes 18 cakes.

title: chicken cordon bleu with white wine sauce
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Lay out flat and sprinkle with parsley.
Top each breast with slice of cheese and 1/2 slice of ham.
Roll up tightly.
Stir together mayonnaise and water in shallow dish.
Roll each bundle in mayonnaise mixture and then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray. Arrange bundles, seam side down, in a single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned, cooked through and cheese is melted.
Serve with White Wine Sauce and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.
One of our favorites!

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump pineapple in the pan and even out. Dump cherry pie filling in the pan and even out. Spread the dry cake mix evenly over pineapple and cherry pie filling. Spread the nuts over the mix and slice the butter in blocks. Lay them in different places over the nuts. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Ready to eat when cooled.

title: mom's fish
directions: Drizzle fish with lemon juice; let sit.

Put in baking pan. Mix mayonnaise, dill weed and 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Brush on one side and grill or broil. Turn fish and brush on the other side; cook (5 to 8 minutes per side depending on thickness of fish).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese as directed on box. Use 1/2 cup milk instead of 1/4 cup.
Brown meat and onion. Drain off grease.
Add Ragu sauce.
Take half the macaroni and cheese and put it on the bottom of the baking dish.
Pour meat mixture on top, then put rest of macaroni and cheese on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut a 1/2-inch slice from the top of each tomato.
Carefully scoop out pulp.
Chop pulp and set aside. Place tomato shells upside down to drain.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pour over the uncooked meat. Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: raisin-caramel pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt and cook down until a rich brown color.
Watch closely.
Add 1 1/2 cups evaporated milk and cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, remaining 1/2 cup evaporated milk and egg yolks (or Egg Beaters) and beat until well blended.
Add raisins; cook and stir until thick and cornstarch is cooked (about 3 or 4 minutes).
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue that follows.

title: zucchini casserole(souffle)
directions: Mix everything together and put in a greased one-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: On medium speed in blender, blend cocoa, creamer, coffee and spices until well blended. Stir in sugar by hand. Use 3 to 4 well rounded teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter; add to other ingredients. Mix well.
Heat and serve.

title: cheddar cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 2 logs or balls; roll into nuts and top with cherry.
Wrap in Saran Wrap or aluminum foil.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: beef onion dip
directions: Cream cheese; add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend in onions and beef.
Mix well.

title: minute rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and soup. Simmer about 5 minutes. Add rice.
After mixture comes to a boil, simmer another few minutes.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Place strips of cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Garnish with olives.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook together broccoli and onion for 5 minutes, then mix with cooked rice, soup and Cheez Whiz and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jam butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until smooth, using an electric mixer. Add flour and baking soda which have been mixed together, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add vanilla. Beat until smooth. Take 1 teaspoon of dough and form a small ball with it. Press your thumb in the center to form a small indentation.
Fill this with raspberry jam.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet lined with foil and slightly greased with Crisco for 15 minutes or until bottom is golden brown.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in boiling water; stir in molasses.
Combine dry cake mix and ginger in a large mixer bowl. Blend in molasses mixture.
Add eggs and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.

title: microwave jello mochi
directions: Dissolve jello in water and stir well.
Add sugar and mochiko mixture to jello liquid and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into 12-inch microwave Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Remove plastic wrap and cool.
Slice with plastic knife.
Dip mochi in 1/2 cup potato starch.
Shake off excess starch.
Yield:
30 pieces.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Spread broccoli in dish.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, Bisquick, butter and eggs with hand beater for 1 minute.
Pour over broccoli. Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into 2 small balls or one large ball.
Roll cheese balls in remaining chopped dried beef.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pour spaghetti sauce over cooked chicken in a baking dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over it.
Heat oven to 375° and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and heat 5-10 minutes more.
Serve with salad, vegetables and garlic bread for a great meal.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Remove casing from linguica and
saute in olive oil.
Add red bell pepper, onion, garlic and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper and saute mixture until translucent.
Add chicken broth and heat to boiling.
Add kale, bay leaves and parsley; return to boil.
Lower heat and add beans and red pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Put in greased casserole.
Heat soup and cream cheese until cheese is melted.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli and mix.
Heat in oven at 350° until hot and bubbly. Serves 8.

title: special syrup sundae
directions: Top double scoops of vanilla ice cream with delicious Griffin's Waffle Syrup.
Heated or straight out of the bottle it's a topping that's hard to beat for a quick delightful sundae.
Make it even more enjoyable by sprinkling pecans over the top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate mixture for about 30 minutes and it will shape into ball easier.
Roll ball in chopped nuts and serve with crackers.

title: tapioca and figs
directions: Stir salt and tapioca into boiling water very slowly.
Use long handled wooden spoon, or it will sometimes pop on your hand. Cook until tapioca is almost transparent.
Add brown sugar, finely cut figs and raisins.
Cook a few more minutes, until fruit is tender.
Add fruit juices and nuts; cook a minute or 2 longer. Cool and serve in sauce dishes with whipped cream or Cool Whip. This is a large recipe, but can be cut in half.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix altogether and beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30
minutes more.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt to dissolved Jell-O.
Cool.
When mixture begins to set, add cranberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into individual molds or small ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes six servings.

title: homemade soup
directions: Put cold water in a No. 12 washpot and the lye starts the water boiling.
After it boils, a fire is lighted beneath the pot and the other ingredients are added.
The process is called saponification.
You keep stirring the ingredients to give the soap the right texture and smoothness.
The rosin takes out the odor.
Handle it very carefully because lye is dangerous to the eyes.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp.
Melt butter in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until soft, about 6 minutes.
Stir in garlic and smoked sausage; saute 5 minutes.
Chop drained tomatoes; stir in and cook 2 minutes.
With a fork, stir in rice to blend.
Add shrimp and seasonings.
Pour tomato liquid over all.
Bring to a boil
Do not stir.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes over low heat.
Serves 4.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening until it is creamed very smooth; add sugar and cream.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Add one cup flour with 1/2 cup milk.
Add the third cup of flour last. Cream well.
Add flavorings.
Pour in a well greased tube pan. Also put flour in dust out all left in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Stir frequently.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch casserole baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Top with onions (optional).
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes, or until knife comes out clean, but still has a custard consistency.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in salt and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add the flour a bit at a time and beat very, very, very well.
Pour into a greased, floured tube pan or bread pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until a straw or knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 1 small cake.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour on cake mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken dinner in a pot
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large, heavy ovenware pot.
Peel potatoes and slice 1/2 inch thick.
Place on top of chicken.
Peel onion and quarter it.
Peel carrots; quarter lengthwise and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Cut ends off green beans or separate frozen green beans.
Place all vegetables in pot.
Sprinkle with parsley. Season with pepper.
Pour sherry over all.
Cover tightly.
Cook at 300° for 2 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli blend
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain well; set aside.
Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Put in greased 1-quart baking dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease shortbread mold. If mold is very complex, a spray on vegetable oil is easier. Beat the butter and sugar together until well mixed and fluffy. Work in flour, cornstarch and salt with fork until mixture holds together and is smooth. Spread mixture in the mold and press firmly. Bake about 45 minutes until golden brown and still just slightly springy in the middle. Turn shortcake out onto a wire rack to cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars and pudding.
Mix in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: speedy sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add soup (do not dilute), relish, ketchup and barbecue sauce. Simmer 10 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by measuring tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute, remove to rack, cool completely.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and have fun.

title: fast holiday gravy
directions: Combine flour and water in medium bowl and stir until it forms a paste.
Stir in broth until mixture is smooth.
Place bowl in microwave on Highest setting for 5 minutes, stirring mixture two times.
Put into slow cooker or in saucepan on top of stove; add chicken
or turkey and eggs.
Simmer until all ingredients are blended.
Add water if it gets too thick.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Flour chicken pieces.
Brown in oil.
Add onion . Mix garlic and mushrooms.
Add to chicken.
Mix soy sauce, catsup, white wine and mushroom juice.
Pour over chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
I've found that any more than 8 pieces of chicken require doubling the recipe.

title: granny's cocoa pudding
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients into 1 2/3 cups boiling water. Pour into baking dish and let stand.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick delicious corn chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Cook potato in chicken broth.
Add the corn and evaporated milk.
Heat and season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candied chex mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except M&M's. Melt almond bark on 1/2 power in microwave until melted. Coat cereal mixture. Add M&M's last. Continue to coat (might have to mix with hands). Spread out on wax paper until cool, then break apart. Store in airtight container.

title: cream of mushroom with chicken
directions: Mix soup and wine and pour over chicken cutlet.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese over each cutlet.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon extra gravy over noodles.

title: gator ollie's black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; rinse.
Add water to cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
In soup kettle, saute celery and onions with butter until tender.
Blend in flour and parsley and cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in beans and liquid.
Add fried meat grease, scallions, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer 4 hours on low heat; remove bay leaf and any bones.
Puree beans in blender.
Add pureed beans back to broth with wine; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherry filling in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Over this, dump cake mix evenly. Spread nuts over top. Melt butter and pour evenly over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Stir sugar and flour together.
Add milk and egg yolks and heat.
Melt butter in skillet and add coconut.
Brown coconut and add to hot mixture when mixture thickens.
Add flavoring and pour in pie shell.
Beat egg whites and brown.

title: oma's pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chopped celery into roasting pan. Arrange pork chops on top of celery. Spread brown mustard on top of chops. Sprinkle with garlic. Pour tomato sauce over chops. Bake in oven at 350° until tender.

title: fudgy caramel apples
directions: Remove stems from apples.
Then insert a wooden stick.
Put the butter and the water in bowl.
Boil until butter melts, then heat the caramels until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Keep caramel mixture over hot water.
Dip apples in caramel and then dip in nuts, then set for storage.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together dry ingredients and raisins and moisten together with egg whites, honey, milk and butter.
Stir only to blend. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan blisters
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, a little at a time, until sugar is melted.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave for additional 20 minutes.

title: three step pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.

title: good hamburger
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let
stand
for 15 minutes.
Make out hamburgers and put on cookie sheet.
Broil in oven until done.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat, at medium speed, butter, sugar and cinnamon 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly. Add eggs.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl as needed, until mixture is light and fluffy, 2 minutes.
Fold in pineapple, bread cubes and pecans.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Place sliced tomatoes in a large shallow dish.
Arrange onion slices over tomatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over tomatoes and onion rings. Cover; refrigerate several hours.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put in a blender and process until smooth.
Will keep in refrigerator 6 days.
One and 1/2 cup mixture equals a 14-ounce can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread crumbs in mixing bowl.
Add extract and water.
Mix to a smooth paste.
Press into a 7 to 8-inch pie pan using the back of a teaspoon.
If it is difficult to mold, wet the back of the spoon with a little water.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crab stew
directions: Saute celery, green onions and bell pepper in butter.
Add other ingredients and heat.
Serve with crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together (in blender) and pour into a large pie pan that has been buttered and floured.
Bake in a preheated oven on 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Pie is done when blade inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
This pie is simple and makes its own crust while baking.

title: crunchy beef noodle casserole
directions: Finely chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Mince garlic. Brown with ground chuck.
Drain.

title: old fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Mash berries.
Add sugar to taste.
Layer pie crust alternately with berries.
Serve with whipped topping.
(I have made this with dewberries or blackberries.)
Easy and so delicious.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mandi's favorite popcorn balls
directions: Stir and cook sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until soft ball stage.
Add vanilla.
Pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well and be sure to coat corn well.
Grease hands with butter and shape into balls.

title: seven-up cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour alternately with each egg, mixing well.
Add lemon flavor, then add 7-Up (warm, not hot); mix thoroughly.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 75 minutes or until tested done.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: terrific chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, Nestle Choco-Bake and vanilla extract until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture alternately with milk. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and lettuce in large bowl.
Toss to blend well.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
To serve, add cheese and spoon onto lettuce. This is great for those sultry summer Beaufort evenings.

title: quick and easy jello
directions: Beat Dream Whip, follow directions on package.
Add cream cheese and 1 package dry jello.
Mix well.
Drain some of the juice off the crushed pineapple.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put in refrigerator.

title: german apple tort
directions: Beat eggs until light yellow; gradually add sugar.
Fold in flour and baking powder.
Fold in apples and a cup of chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chutney
directions: Mix and cook slowly until soft and thick, about 2 hours. Bottle.
Good with hamburgers, hot dogs and any meat dish.

title: spinach rollups
directions: Stir together the first 6 ingredients.
Spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll up, jelly-roll fashion, pressing edges to seal. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 4-6 hours.
Cut into 1/2 inch thick slices.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: banana-apricot nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar, apricots and nuts until thoroughly blended.
In a separate bowl, combine bananas, milk, egg whites and yogurt; stir into dry ingredients just until well blended.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven (325° for glass pan) for 1 1/4 hours or until bread begins to pull away from sides of pan and toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes; turn out onto a rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done, stirring to break up into small pieces.
Drain well on paper towels.
Salt and pepper lightly. Allow to cool.
Combine beef, drained beans, onion, chilies, tomatoes and olives.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until brown and crumbly. Drain well. Add half of the spaghetti sauce to the skillet. Pour diced tomatoes evenly over ground beef. Combine Ricotta and egg in a small bowl; mix well. Spread over tomatoes. Top with a layer of lasagna noodles. Layer the remaining spaghetti sauce and remaining noodles in the skillet. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes, until noodles are tender. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and cook for 2 to 3 more minutes.

title: raisin nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add raisins, liquid and vanilla.
Beat together.
Add flour, baking powder and walnuts alternately.
Beat together and put into well greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: breakfast savory sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Add green peppers, onion and celery; saute until vegetables are slightly tender.
Cook grits in boiling salt water 5 minutes.
Combine grits and sausage mixture.
Pour into buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spread undiluted soup over sausage mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tempura(japan)
directions: At first drop egg into bowl then water, flour, baking powder and salt (all together).
Mix until moist like a soft dough.
Next slice vegetables; dip into dough.
Then deep fry (until golden brown).

title: phil's phood
directions: Boil pasta as package directs; drain and mix with other ingredients.
(For a more healthy version, add more vegetables and less mayonnaise.)
Serve hot or cold.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add walnuts, celery, coconut, marshmallows, pineapple and grapes.
Add a few grains of salt and lemon juice to the salad dressing.
Pour over apple mixture.

title: homemade grape juice
directions: Fill jar with 1 cup grapes.
Add the sugar and fill to top of jar with boiling water.
Seal jars and process 10 to 15 minutes. Let stand 2 weeks before using.
Strain grapes and enjoy.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream first 7 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into container and freeze.
Cut in squares when ready to serve.

title: broccoli cornbread(this is delicious!)
directions: Combine 1st seven ingredients; mix well by hand.
Melt butter in a glass oblong casserole dish.
Pour mixture in the margarine. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken loaf
directions: Remove chicken from bones. Chop finely. Mix chicken with 1 3/4 cups crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper, milk and eggs. Stir in butter. Pour in loaf pan. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In large skillet, scramble sausage until brown.
Mix in eggs, salt and pepper; scramble until done.
Heat tortillas (buttered on inside lightly) in microwave or on griddle.
Dip egg and sausage onto hot tortilla.
Add picante sauce and cheese.
Roll and serve. Serves 4.

title: light trifle
directions: Pour milk into bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended, stirring in 3 cups of whipped topping.
Place half the cake cubes in a large trifle dish.
Top with half the fruit.
Spread pudding mixture over fruit.
Top with remaining cake cubes and fruit.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve. Makes 12 servings, each with 160 calories and 3 grams fat.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Place 2 baking sheets with corn tortillas overlapping (coat both sides of tortillas with cooking spray) in oven. Bake 7 minutes; flip tortillas over. Rotate pans. Bake until lightly brown, 7 minutes. In large nonstick skillet, brown round sirloin, breaking up clumps.
Stir in green and red peppers. Add taco seasoning. Cook 4 minutes. Spread tortillas with refried beans or you could use bean dip.
Top each with heaping 1/4 cup meat and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Bake 2 minutes to melt cheese.

title: broccoli casserole(no rice)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients.
Put broccoli into buttered casserole dish and pour mixture over broccoli evenly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Take out of oven and spread grated cheese.
Put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream together the zucchini, sugar, salt, oil and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 32 servings.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: To prepare pan, use 10 x 14 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan.
Butter pan generously.
Pour peaches into pan.
Use all the juice.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients and then add hot water; cool to lukewarm.
Mix in rye flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Add white flour.
Knead dough 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch and let rise again.
Form into 2 loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit topped cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar until creamy.
Mix in topping.
Spoon into crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours. Garnish with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of a double boiler. Place it over boiling water and beat with rotary beater for exactly 7 minutes. Cool. Add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: sunrise punch
directions: Empty drink mix into large plastic or glass pitcher.
Add water and pineapple juice.
Stir until drink mix is dissolved. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Pour into punch bowl just before serving.
Stir in 1 bottle chilled club soda.
Serve over ice cubes.
Makes 8 1-cup servings.

title: creamy gelatin salad
directions: Use food processor and cream the entire carton of cottage cheese to the consistency of sour cream.
A blender will work, but does not cream the cottage cheese as smooth as food processor. Mix gelatin following package directions for dissolving; do not add second cup of water.
Set dissolved gelatin aside to cool. Add sour cream to creamed cottage cheese and mix well.
Add gelatin to cottage cheese mixture.
Add sweetener or sugar and mix.
Fold in fruit.
Pour in large glass casserole and place in refrigerator to chill.
Take at least 2 hours to set.
Entire recipe makes 8 servings.

title: glorified dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in the undrained pineapple. Push around to cover bottom of pan evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
Then dump the cake mix over this.
Sprinkle sugar, chopped nuts and miniature marshmallows over the mix.
Dot with margarine (1 to 2 sticks, depending on how rich you want it). Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream as topping.

title: 15 minute beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and cut in small pieces.
Heat fat in skillet until you have 3 Tbsp. melted.
Brown meat quickly.
Add water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix and heat until boiling. Blend sour cream and flour; add to meat mixture.
Cook and stir until thickens.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: raspberry almond squares
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add butter, sugars, vanilla and egg yolk.
Press dough into sheet pan.
Spread preserves evenly over top.
Lightly beat egg white and brush lightly over top.
Sprinkle with nuts, pressing gently.
Bake at 300° until edges are brown and center is firm (30 to 35 minutes).
Remove from oven.
Loosen sides with spatula immediately.
Cut in squares.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown sausage; reserve grease (there will be very little if you use Rice's brand).
Set sausage aside.
Saute onion, half of the green pepper and the 2 jalapeno peppers in sausage drippings. Add enough flour to thicken.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over mixture.
Add the juice from the 2 cans of hominy and half cup milk.
Blend until smooth and thickened.
Add hominy and sausage and reheat.
Pour into a casserole and let set overnight.
Top with green pepper rings, grated cheese and crumbled Doritos chips. Heat at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad. It's better than tacos in the shell.

title: raspberry cobbler(no-fat - no cholesterol)
directions: Place berries in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and milk; pour on top of berries.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top of dough.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry and apple milk shake
directions: In a medium bowl, using a whisk or large fork, combine milk and apple juice concentrate until they are smooth.
You can also shake them in a jar with a tight fitting cover. With a small spoon, stir the yogurt. Add it to the milk and apple juice concentrate.
Stir or shake until smooth and blended.

title: confections pound cake
directions: In large bowl or mixer beat butter until creamy.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually and gently stir in flour, blending just until flour is thoroughly incorporated.
Turn into well-buttered and lightly floured 3-quart fluted or plain tube pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven 1 1/2 hours or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with vanilla confectioners sugar.
Makes 24 slices.

title: overnight crunch coffee cake
directions: Combine.
Sprinkle over batter.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: black bean mexican pizza
directions: Bake for 7 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Serve with salsa.
Also, mix 1/2 cup fat free sour cream with 1/4 cup taco sauce to serve on side.

title: deluxe fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add honey, flour, candied fruit and orange peel.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Glaze with 2 parts honey and 1 part water. Yields 3 loaves.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Put mixture in pan. Beat Bisquick, milk and egg until smooth.
Pour over beef. Bake about 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top. When cheese is melted, garnish top with lettuce and tomato.

title: chicken and curly pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta until limp.
Drain.
Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Combine chicken broth and cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in Pet milk and both cream soups until well blended.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
If pasta starts to dry out too much, cover very loosely with foil.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil and 1/2 cup cold water, prunes, egg and vanilla.
Blend and beat 1 minute at medium speed. Pour in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top of batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion in skillet and drain off fat. Mix with rest of ingredients in a crock-pot and simmer for 1 hour. Keep warm and serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese together.
Add the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham crust.
Chill in freezer.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, parsley and salt.
Melt butter, mustard and Worcestershire with garlic clove in saucepan. Dip chicken in butter mix, then crumbs.
Bake at 350° in shallow baking pan for 1 hour.

title: chicken, wild rice and tomato salad
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet or wok.
Add onion and celery; saute until tender.
Add chicken, wild rice, peas and parsley to skillet.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add seasonings and add to skillet.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and tomatoes, tossing to blend ingredients.
Serve immediately while warm.

title: overnight bloody mary
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Yield: 15 1/2 cup servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each.
Sift soda, salt and flour.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Add apples, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven while cake is baking.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Place sliced squash into casserole dish (2 slices thick).
Top with layer of sliced tomatoes then 3 slices of onion rings. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and Parmesan cheese to taste. Continue layers to 1 inch from the top of dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then cheese and a thin layer of bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue cooking for 15 minutes to brown top.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Stuff each chicken breast with a mixture of Jack cheese and green peppers equally. Roll up chicken breasts and secure tightly with toothpicks. Roll each breast in egg mixture, then dredge in corn meal. Place in greased casserole dish. Spread enchilada sauce over each breast. Put remaining Jack cheese on top of each breast. Sprinkle on olives. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly and chicken is cooked through. Serves 6.

title: baked bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook (slow) on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put margarine, shortening, water and cocoa in saucepan; heat over low
heat
until
margarine
melts.
Mix well flour, sugar and salt;
add to mixture.	Add soda to buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Then add to mixture.
Bake in layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a vegetable dip.

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, hamburger meat and onions in greased casserole (season).
Pour soup over and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Add other ingredients.
Line casserole with buttered crumbs.
Pour in mixture and just before removing from oven, top with more buttered crumbs and brown.
Cook 1/2 hour at 350°.
Use about 1/4 package of crumbs.
Drain squash well.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Thaw potatoes and place in buttered Pyrex baking dish.
Heat rest of ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and celery.
Spoon off fat; add salt and pepper.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Spread mixture in baking dish and pour undiluted soup over everything.
Top with layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly at 400°.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add egg, oil and milk. Beat until
smooth.
Pour
into well-greased muffin tins or a medium skillet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven back to
400° and bake 20 more minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 medium size muffins.

title: oven-browned chicken
directions: Melt butter in large, flat-bottomed baking pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings.
Place in baking dish and brown, skin side down, for 25 minutes at 400° in oven.
Turn pieces and brown 25 more minutes.

title: dad's chicken 'n rice
directions: In frying pan, melt margarine.
Add garlic and diced chicken. Cook chicken until it turns white.
Add soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice. (Chinese noodles are great on top.)
Serves 6.
